173/* Fortran error indices do not match SCC, and this file will always use error
174 * numbers specified by our C compiler.
175 */
176#define ERR_OFFSET 700
177
178/* Error routine.
179 * Preprocessor error codes less than 200 are assumed to be identical in both
180 * Fortran and C compilers, except for error 23.
181 */
182#define pperror(n, x, sev) \
183 do { \
184 if (ERR_OFFSET && (n) == 23) \
185 error(236, sev, startline, x, CNULL); \
186 else if ((n) < 200) \
187 error((n), sev, startline, x, CNULL); \
188 else \
189 error((n) + ERR_OFFSET, sev, startline, x, CNULL); \
190 } while (0)
191
192#define pperr(n, sev) pperror(n, CNULL, sev)

322/*
323 * Tokens for parser.
324 * Preprocessor constants must be interpreted as long (Standard 3.8.1).
325 * When a long is the same size as an int (32 bits), it's sufficient to use
326 * tobinary() and to represent constant expressions as ints. When a long is
327 * larger than an int, such as a 64-bit int, all constant expressions are
328 * represented as a 64-bit value; tobinary64() is used to convert decimal
329 * values into the 64-bit representation.
330 *
331 * There will be two sets of definitions for the parser token value and
332 * macros representing the operations on a token value - the selection
333 * is based on whether or not PPNUM_IS_32 is defined.
334 */
335
336#if LONG_IS_64
337#undef PPNUM_IS_32
338#else
339#undef PPNUM_IS_32
340#define PPNUM_IS_32
341#endif
342
343/*
344 * c99 apparently defines a preprocessor number to be
345 * any C number and any preprocessing integer arithmetic is defined to
346 * be computed as intmax_t/uintmax_t values. These types are typically
347 * 64-bit types, so since pgcc supports 'long long':
348 */
349#undef PPNUM_IS_32

351#if defined(PPNUM_IS_32)

355typedef struct {
356 INT val;
357 int isuns;
358} PTOK;
359#define PTOK_V(t) t.val
360#define PTOK_VUNS(a) (UINT) PTOK_V(a)
361#define PTOK_ISUNS(t) t.isuns
362#else
363typedef struct {
364 DBLINT64 val;
365 int isuns;
366} PTOK;
367#define PTOK_V(t) (t).val
368#define PTOK_VUNS(a) (UINT *) PTOK_V(a)
369#define PTOK_ISUNS(t) (t).isuns
370#endif
371/*
372 * Define macros to perform misc. operations, generally of the form:
373 * a = a <op> b
374 * Two sets of definitions are possible:
375 * 1. sizeof(long) == sizeof(int)
376 * 2. sizeof(long) > sizeof(int)
377 *
378 * Note that for #2 on the ST100, only the rightmost 40 bits are significant.
379 */
380#if defined(PPNUM_IS_32)
381#define PTOK_MUL(a, b) PTOK_V(a) *= PTOK_V(b)
382#define PTOK_DIV(a, b) PTOK_V(a) /= PTOK_V(b)
383#define PTOK_UDIV(a, b) \
384 { \
385 UINT ui; \
386 udiv(PTOK_VUNS(a), PTOK_VUNS(b), ui); \
387 PTOK_V(a) = ui; \
388 }
389
390#define PTOK_MOD(a, b) PTOK_V(a) %= PTOK_V(b)
391#define PTOK_UMOD(a, b) \
392 { \
393 UINT ui; \
394 umod(PTOK_VUNS(a), PTOK_VUNS(b), ui); \
395 PTOK_V(a) = ui; \
396 }
397
398#define PTOK_ADD(a, b) PTOK_V(a) += PTOK_V(b)
399#define PTOK_SUB(a, b) PTOK_V(a) -= PTOK_V(b)
400#define PTOK_NEG(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = -PTOK_V(b)
401
402#define PTOK_AND(a, b) PTOK_V(a) &= PTOK_V(b)
403#define PTOK_OR(a, b) PTOK_V(a) |= PTOK_V(b)
404#define PTOK_XOR(a, b) PTOK_V(a) ^= PTOK_V(b)
405#define PTOK_BNOT(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = ~PTOK_V(b)
406#define PTOK_LNOT(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = !PTOK_V(b)
407#define PTOK_ANDAND(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = (PTOK_V(a) && PTOK_V(b))
408#define PTOK_OROR(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = (PTOK_V(a) || PTOK_V(b))
409
410#define PTOK_LSHIFT(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = LSHIFT(PTOK_V(a), PTOK_V(b))
411#define PTOK_URSHIFT(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = URSHIFT(PTOK_V(a), PTOK_V(b))
412#define PTOK_CRSHIFT(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = CRSHIFT(PTOK_V(a), PTOK_V(b))
413
414#define PTOK_LOGEQ(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = PTOK_V(a) == PTOK_V(b)
415#define PTOK_LOGNE(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = PTOK_V(a) != PTOK_V(b)
416#define PTOK_LOGLT(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = PTOK_V(a) < PTOK_V(b)
417#define PTOK_LOGLE(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = PTOK_V(a) <= PTOK_V(b)
418#define PTOK_LOGGT(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = PTOK_V(a) > PTOK_V(b)
419#define PTOK_LOGGE(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = PTOK_V(a) >= PTOK_V(b)
420
421#define PTOK_UCMP(a, b) ucmp(PTOK_VUNS(a), PTOK_VUNS(b))
422#define PTOK_LOGULT(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = PTOK_UCMP(a, b) < 0
423#define PTOK_LOGULE(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = PTOK_UCMP(a, b) <= 0
424#define PTOK_LOGUGT(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = PTOK_UCMP(a, b) > 0
425#define PTOK_LOGUGE(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = PTOK_UCMP(a, b) >= 0
426
427#define PTOK_ISNEG(a) (PTOK_V(a) < 0)
428#define PTOK_ISNZ(a) (PTOK_V(a) != 0)
429#define PTOK_ASSN(a, b) PTOK_V(a) = PTOK_V(b)

431/* Misc. operations on the lsp (least significant portion) of a token; e.g.,
432 * ASSN32 - lsp = int; clear the most significant portion
433 * LSHIFT32 - lsp <<= int
434 * OR32 - lsp |= int
435 * BTEST32 - test the bits of the lsp
436 * SEXTEND32 - signextend the lsp into the most significant portion
437 */
438#define PTOK_ASSN32(a, i) PTOK_V(a) = (i)
439#define PTOK_LSHIFT32(a, i) PTOK_V(a) <<= (i)
440#define PTOK_OR32(a, i) PTOK_V(a) |= (i)
441#define PTOK_BTEST32(a, i) (PTOK_V(a) & (i))
442#define PTOK_SEXTEND32(a)
443#else
444/* LONG_IS_64 PTOK macro defs */

447#define MKXUL(a)

449static DBLINT64 zero64 = {0, 0};
450static void mod64(DBLINT64, DBLINT64, DBLINT64);
451static void umod64(DBLUINT64, DBLUINT64, DBLUINT64);
452
453#define PTOK_MUL(a, b) mul64(PTOK_V(a), PTOK_V(b), PTOK_V(a)) MKXUL(a)
454#define PTOK_DIV(a, b) div64(PTOK_V(a), PTOK_V(b), PTOK_V(a))
455#define PTOK_UDIV(a, b) \
456 { \
457 DBLUINT64 ui; \
458 udiv64(PTOK_VUNS(a), PTOK_VUNS(b), ui); \
459 PTOK_V(a)[0] = ui[0]; \
460 PTOK_V(a)[1] = ui[1]; \
461 FIXUL(a); \
462 }
463
464#define PTOK_MOD(a, b) mod64(PTOK_V(a), PTOK_V(b), PTOK_V(a))
465#define PTOK_UMOD(a, b) \
466 umod64(PTOK_VUNS(a), PTOK_VUNS(b), PTOK_VUNS(a)) MKXUL(a)
467
468#define PTOK_ADD(a, b) add64(PTOK_V(a), PTOK_V(b), PTOK_V(a)) MKXUL(a)
469#define PTOK_SUB(a, b) sub64(PTOK_V(a), PTOK_V(b), PTOK_V(a)) MKXUL(a)
470#define PTOK_NEG(a, b) neg64(PTOK_V(b), PTOK_V(a)) MKXUL(a)
471
472#define PTOK_AND(a, b) and64(PTOK_V(a), PTOK_V(b), PTOK_V(a)) MKXUL(a)
473#define PTOK_OR(a, b) or64(PTOK_V(a), PTOK_V(b), PTOK_V(a)) MKXUL(a)
474#define PTOK_XOR(a, b) xor64(PTOK_V(a), PTOK_V(b), PTOK_V(a)) MKXUL(a)
475#define PTOK_BNOT(a, b) not64(PTOK_V(b), PTOK_V(a)) MKXUL(a)
476#define PTOK_LNOT(a, b) PTOK_ASSN32(a, cmp64(PTOK_V(b), zero64) == 0)
477#define PTOK_ANDAND(a, b) \
478 PTOK_ASSN32(a, cmp64(PTOK_V(a), zero64) && cmp64(PTOK_V(b), zero64))
479#define PTOK_OROR(a, b) \
480 PTOK_ASSN32(a, cmp64(PTOK_V(a), zero64) || cmp64(PTOK_V(b), zero64))
481
482#define PTOK_LSHIFT(a, b) shf64(PTOK_V(a), PTOK_V(b)[1], PTOK_V(a)) MKXUL(a)
483#define PTOK_URSHIFT(a, b) \
484 ushf64(PTOK_VUNS(a), -PTOK_V(b)[1], PTOK_VUNS(a)) MKXUL(a)
485#define PTOK_CRSHIFT(a, b) shf64(PTOK_V(a), -PTOK_V(b)[1], PTOK_V(a)) MKXUL(a)
486
487#define PTOK_CMP(a, b) cmp64(PTOK_V(a), PTOK_V(b))
488#define PTOK_LOGEQ(a, b) PTOK_ASSN32(a, PTOK_CMP(a, b) == 0)
489#define PTOK_LOGNE(a, b) PTOK_ASSN32(a, PTOK_CMP(a, b) != 0)
490#define PTOK_LOGLT(a, b) PTOK_ASSN32(a, PTOK_CMP(a, b) < 0)
491#define PTOK_LOGLE(a, b) PTOK_ASSN32(a, PTOK_CMP(a, b) <= 0)
492#define PTOK_LOGGT(a, b) PTOK_ASSN32(a, PTOK_CMP(a, b) > 0)
493#define PTOK_LOGGE(a, b) PTOK_ASSN32(a, PTOK_CMP(a, b) >= 0)
494
495#define PTOK_UCMP(a, b) ucmp64(PTOK_VUNS(a), PTOK_VUNS(b))
496#define PTOK_LOGULT(a, b) PTOK_ASSN32(a, PTOK_UCMP(a, b) < 0)
497#define PTOK_LOGULE(a, b) PTOK_ASSN32(a, PTOK_UCMP(a, b) <= 0)
498#define PTOK_LOGUGT(a, b) PTOK_ASSN32(a, PTOK_UCMP(a, b) > 0)
499#define PTOK_LOGUGE(a, b) PTOK_ASSN32(a, PTOK_UCMP(a, b) >= 0)
500
501#define PTOK_ISNEG(a) (cmp64(PTOK_V(a), zero64) < 0)
502#define PTOK_ISNZ(a) (cmp64(PTOK_V(a), zero64) != 0)
503#define PTOK_ASSN(a, b) \
504 (void)(PTOK_V(a)[0] = PTOK_V(b)[0], PTOK_V(a)[1] = PTOK_V(b)[1])

506/* Misc. operations on the lsp (least significant portion) of a token; e.g.,
507 * ASSN32 - lsp = int; clear the most significant portion
508 * LSHIFT32 - lsp <<= int
509 * OR32 - lsp |= int
510 * BTEST32 - test the bits of the lsp
511 * SEXTEND32 - signextend the lsp into the most significant portion
512 */
513#define PTOK_ASSN32(a, i) (void)(PTOK_V(a)[1] = (i), PTOK_V(a)[0] = 0)
514#define PTOK_LSHIFT32(a, i) PTOK_V(a)[1] <<= (i)
515#define PTOK_OR32(a, i) PTOK_V(a)[1] |= (i)
516#define PTOK_BTEST32(a, i) (PTOK_V(a)[1] & (i))
517#define PTOK_SEXTEND32(a) \
518 { \
519 if (PTOK_V(a)[1] & 0x80000000) \
520 PTOK_V(a)[0] = 0xffffffff; \
521 else \
522 PTOK_V(a)[0] = 0; \
523 }
524#endif

596#define GROW_ARGBUF(argbuf, argp, fstart, argbufsize, newsize) \
597 { \
598 int poffset = argp - argbuf; \
599 int foffset = fstart - argbuf; \
600 NEED(argbufsize + 1, argbuf, char, argbufsize, newsize); \
601 argp = argbuf + poffset; \
602 fstart = argbuf + foffset; \
603 }

658static int
659skipbl(char *tokval, int flag)
660{
661 int toktyp;
662
663 for (toktyp = gtok(tokval, flag); iswhite(toktyp);
664 toktyp = gtok(tokval, flag))
665 ;
666
667 return toktyp;
668}

670/** \brief
671 * Replaces fprintf (ff, format, str) ,
672 * - checks for spaces in the string,
673 * - and windows ':'
674 * - and adds backspaces so that the output can be included in makefiles
675 */
676void
677print_and_check(FILE *ff, char *str, char end_c)
678{
679 char *cp;
680 char ch;
681
682 for (cp = str; *cp; ++cp) {
683 ch = *cp;
684 if (ch == ' ')
685 fputc('\\', ff);
686#if defined(TARGET_WIN)
687 /* c: changed to \c */
688 if (isalpha(ch) && *(cp + 1) && *(cp + 1) == ':') {
689 fprintf(ff, "/%c", ch);
690 ++cp;
691 } else
692#endif
693
694 fputc(ch, ff);
695 }
696 if (end_c)
697 fputc(end_c, ff);
698}

700static void acc_display_macros()
701{
702 unsigned int i;
703 for (i = 1U; i < next_hash; ++i) {
704 char *name = &deftab[hashrec[i].name];
705 char *value = &deftab[hashrec[i].value];
706 if ((strncmp(name, "__LINE__", 8) == 0) ||
707 (strncmp(name, "__DATE__", 8) == 0) ||
708 (strncmp(name, "__FILE__", 8) == 0) ||
709 (strncmp(name, "__TIME__", 8) == 0)) continue;
710 fprintf(gbl.outfil, "%s : %s\n", name, value);
711 }
712}

714void
715accpp(void)
716{
717 int toktyp;
718 char *p;
719 PPSYM *sp;
720 char **cp;
721 int done;
722 int i;
723 INT mon;
724 char tokval[TOKMAX];
725 char **dirp;
726 static char adate[] = "\"Mmm dd yyyy\"";
727 static const char *months[12] = {"Jan", "Feb", "Mar", "Apr", "May", "Jun",
728 "Jul", "Aug", "Sep", "Oct", "Nov", "Dec"};
729 static char atime[] = "\"hh:mm:ss\"";
730
731 cpp_comments = FALSE;
732
733/* -B or -c90x options: Ignore C++ style comments "//" to end-of-line
734 * 'cpp_comments' can only be true for C++, as "//" is the concatenation
735 * operator in Fortran and we pass that on to the lexer in the Fortran case.
736 */
737
738 if (XBIT(123, 0x100000))
739 ctable['$'] = 0;
740
741 startline = -1;
742 list_flag = flg.list;
743 pflag = flg.es && !flg.p;
744
745 NEW(inclstack, INCLSTACK, MAXINC);
746 incsize = MAXINC;
747
748 NEW(_ifs, IFREC, IFMAX);
749 ifsize = IFMAX;
750
751 strcpy(inclstack[0].fname, gbl.file_name);
752 dirnam(inclstack[0].fname, inclstack[0].dirname);
753 gbl.curr_file = gbl.file_name;
754 inclstack[0].ifp = gbl.srcfil;
755 inclstack[0].lineno = 0;
756 inclstack[0].count = 1;
757 inclstack[0].from_stdinc = FALSE;
758 ifp = inclstack[0].ifp;
759
760 linelen = LINELEN;
761 linesize = (linelen + linelen);
762 NEW(linebuf, char, linesize);
763
764 lineptr = lineend = linebuf + linelen;
765
766/* process def and undef command line options */
767
768 for (cp = flg.def; cp && *cp; ++cp) {
769 /* enter it */
770 for (p = *cp; *p && *p != '='; ++p)
771 ;
772 if (!*p) {
773 pbstr("1\n");
774 pbchar(' ');
775 pbstr(*cp);
776 pbchar(' ');
777 dodef(1);
778 } else {
779 char c;
780 c = *p;
781 *p = 0;
782 pbchar('\n');
783 if (p[1] != 0)
784 pbstr(p + 1);
785 pbchar(' ');
786 pbstr(*cp);
787 *p = c;
788 pbchar(' ');
789 dodef(1);
790 }
791 }
792
793/* add ANSI std predefined macros */
794#define chkdef(name, val) \
795 do { \
796 sp = lookup(name, 1); \
797 sp->flags |= F_PREDEF; \
798 sp->nformals = 0; \
799 if (sp->value != 0) \
800 pperror(245, name, 1); \
801 else { \
802 sp->value = strstore(val); \
803 if (XBIT(122, 0x40000)) \
804 putmac(sp); \
805 } \
806 } while(0)
807
808 chkdef("__FLANG", "1");
809
810 chkdef("__LINE__", "0");
811 lineloc = sp - hashrec;
812
813 chkdef("__FILE__", "1");
814 fileloc = sp - hashrec;
815
816 strncpy(&adate[2], gbl.datetime, 10);
817 adate[4] = adate[7] = ' '; /* delete '/' */
818 (void)atoxi(&adate[2], &mon, 2, 10);
819 if (adate[5] == '0')
820 adate[5] = ' ';
821 strncpy(&adate[1], months[mon - 1], 3);
822 strncpy(&atime[1], &gbl.datetime[12], 8);
823
824 chkdef("__DATE__", adate);
825 chkdef("__TIME__", atime);
826
827 if (!XBIT(123, 0x400000)) {
828 if (XBIT(123, 0x10) || XBIT(123, 0x80)) { /* -Xa or -Xt */
829 chkdef("__STDC__", "0");
830 } else if (XBIT(122, 2)) { /* -Xs */
831 if ((sp = lookup("__STDC__", 0)) != 0) {
832 if (sp->flags & F_PREDEF) {
833 pperror(246, "__STDC__", 1);
834 sp->flags &= ~F_PREDEF;
835 }
836 delete("__STDC__");
837 }
838 } else {
839#ifdef TARGET_WIN
840 /* Windows uses default -D__STDC__=0, matching Microsoft CL */
841 chkdef("__STDC__", "0");
842#else
843 /* Linux uses default -D__STDC__=1, matching gcc */
844 chkdef("__STDC__", "1");
845 /* Other targets:
846 * SUA ??
847 * OSX ??
848 */
849#endif
850 }
851 }
852
853 if (XBIT(123, 0x80000000)) {
854 if (XBIT(122, 0x400000)) {
855 chkdef("__STDC_VERSION__", "201112L");
856 } else {
857 chkdef("__STDC_VERSION__", "199901L");
858 }
859 }
860
861/* Introduce macros for Fortran (if we are preprocessing Fortran code) */
862
863# define PP_MAJOR "__FLANG_MAJOR__"
864# define PP_MINOR "__FLANG_MINOR__"
865# define PP_PATCHLEVEL "__FLANG_PATCHLEVEL__"
866 if (XBIT(124, 0x200000)) {
867 chkdef("pgi", "1");
868 }
869
870 p = version.vsn;
871 for (i = 0; i < TOKMAX - 1 && isdig(*p); i++)
872 tokval[i] = *p++;
873 tokval[i] = 0;
874 if (i == 0) { /* no digits */
875 chkdef(PP_MAJOR, "99");
876 chkdef(PP_MINOR, "99");
877 } else {
878 while (*p != 0 && !isdig(*p)) /* skip non-digits */
879 p++;
880 chkdef(PP_MAJOR, tokval);
881 for (i = 0; i < TOKMAX - 1 && isdig(*p); i++) tokval[i] = *p++;
882 tokval[i] = 0;
883 if (i == 0) { /* no digits */
884 chkdef(PP_MINOR, "99");
885 } else {
886 chkdef(PP_MINOR, tokval);
887 }
888 }
889 p = version.bld;
890 while (*p != 0 && !isdig(*p)) /* skip non-digits */
891 p++;
892 for (i = 0; i < TOKMAX - 1 && isdig(*p); i++)
893 tokval[i] = *p++;
894 tokval[i] = 0;
895 if (i == 0) { /* no digits */
896 chkdef(PP_PATCHLEVEL, "99");
897 } else {
898 chkdef(PP_PATCHLEVEL, tokval);
899 }
900
901 /* value of _OPENMP is 201307, July, 2013 - version 4.0 */
902 if (flg.smp && !XBIT(69, 1))
903 chkdef("_OPENMP", "201307");
904
905 sp = lookup("defined", 1);
906 sp->flags |= F_PREDEF;
907 sp->nformals = -1;
908
909#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
910 chkdef("__flang_quadfp__", "1");
911#endif
912
913#undef chkdef
914
915/* now undef from command line */
916 for (cp = flg.undef; cp && *cp; ++cp) {
917 /* undef it */
918 if ((sp = lookup(*cp, 0)) != 0) {
919 if (sp->flags & F_PREDEF) {
920 pperror(246, *cp, 1);
921 sp->flags &= ~F_PREDEF;
922 }
923 delete(*cp); /* should check if IDENT */
924 }
925 }
926
927 if (flg.list_macros) {
928 acc_display_macros();
929
930 FREE(deftab);
931 FREE(hashrec);
932 /* FREE(inclstack); Do not free this, gbl.curr_file points to it */
933 FREE(_ifs);
934 FREE(linebuf);
935
936 if (incllist != NULL) {
937 FREE(incllist);
938 }
939
940 flg.es = TRUE;
941 finish();
942 }
943
944 idir.b_avl = 0;
945 idir.b_sz = 2048;
946 NEW(idir.b, char, idir.b_sz);
947
948 idir.cnt = 0;
949 idir.sz = 64;
950 NEW(idir.path, int, idir.sz);
951
952 for (dirp = flg.idir; dirp && *dirp; dirp++)
953 stash_paths(*dirp);
954 if (XBIT(123, 0x1000)) {
955 p = getenv("CPATH");
956 if (p != NULL)
957 stash_paths(p);
958 p = getenv("C_INCLUDE_PATH");
959 if (p != NULL)
960 stash_paths(p);
961 }
962 if (flg.stdinc == 0)
963 stash_paths(DIRSINCS);
964 else if (flg.stdinc != (char *)1)
965 stash_paths(flg.stdinc);
966
967 inclstack[0].path_idx = idir.last = -1;
968
969 /* at this point no predefined macros can be #undef'd */
970 iftop = -1;
971 ifpush();
972 ifstack(truth) = 1;
973 strcpy(cur_fname, inclstack[0].fname);
974 cur_line = 1;
975 cur_from_stdinc = inclstack[0].from_stdinc;
976 nifile = 0;
977 pr_line(cur_fname, cur_line, cur_from_stdinc);
978
979 /* main processing loop */
980 for (;;) {
981 char *s_bl;
982 toktyp = findtok(tokval, ifstack(truth));
983 if (toktyp == EOF)
984 break;
985 s_bl = lineptr;
986 toktyp =
987 skipbl(tokval, 0); /* # JUNK -- JUNK is not subject to macro repl. */
988 done = -1; /* clreol with error message */
989 if (toktyp == '\n') { /* ANSI NULL directive */
990 done = 1; /* no clreol */
991 } else if (toktyp == T_PPNUM) {
992 done = 0;
993 if (ifstack(truth)) {
994 doline(0, tokval);
995 done = 1;
996 }
997 } else if (toktyp != T_IDENT) {
998 if (!XBIT(123, 0x200000)) {
999 /* ansi sez this is an error */
1000 pperr(214, 2);
1001 done = 0; /* clreol with no error message */
1002 } else {
1003 ptok("#");
1004 if (iswhite(*s_bl))
1005 ptok(" "); /* put back one whitespace if any present */
1006 ptok(tokval);
1007 while ((toktyp = gtok(tokval, 1)) != EOF && toktyp != '\n')
1008 ptok(tokval);
1009 done = 1;
1010 }
1011 } else {
1012 switch (dlookup(tokval)) {
1013 case D_IF:
1014 done = 0;
1015 ifpush();
1016 if (_ifs[iftop - 1].truth) {
1017 done = 1;
1018 if (doparse()) {
1019 ifstack(truth) = 1;
1020 ifstack(true_seen) = 1;
1021 } else
1022 ifstack(truth) = 0;
1023 } else
1024 ifstack(truth) = 0;
1025 break;
1026 case D_ELIF:
1027 done = 0;
1028 if (iftop == 0)
1029 pperr(238, 3);
1030 else if (ifstack(else_seen))
1031 pperr(201, 3);
1032 else if (ifstack(true_seen))
1033 ifstack(truth) = 0;
1034 else if (!ifstack(truth) && !ifstack(true_seen) &&
1035 _ifs[iftop - 1].truth) {
1036 done = 1;
1037 if (doparse()) {
1038 ifstack(true_seen) = 1;
1039 ifstack(truth) = 1;
1040 } else
1041 ifstack(truth) = 0;
1042 }
1043 break;
1044 case D_ELSE:
1045 done = 0;
1046 if (iftop == 0)
1047 pperr(239, 3);
1048 else if (ifstack(else_seen))
1049 pperr(202, 3);
1050 else if (ifstack(true_seen))
1051 ifstack(truth) = 0;
1052 else if (!ifstack(truth) && !ifstack(true_seen) &&
1053 _ifs[iftop - 1].truth) {
1054 ifstack(true_seen) = 1;
1055 ifstack(truth) = 1;
1056 }
1057 if (iftop > 0)
1058 ifstack(else_seen) = 1;
1059 break;
1060 case D_ENDIF:
1061 done = 0;
1062 if (iftop == 0)
1063 pperr(240, 3);
1064 else
1065 --iftop;
1066 break;
1067 case D_IFDEF:
1068 done = -1;
1069 /* ANS X3.159-1989: #ifdef have only one identifier
1070 done = 0;
1071 */
1072 ifpush(); /* sets truth value to old truth value */
1073 toktyp = skipbl(tokval, 0);
1074 if (toktyp != T_IDENT) {
1075 pperr(231, 2);
1076 ifstack(truth) = 0;
1077 if (toktyp == '\n')
1078 done = 1;
1079 } else if (lookup(tokval, 0) == 0)
1080 ifstack(truth) = 0;
1081 else {
1082 ifstack(truth) &= 1;
1083 ifstack(true_seen) = 1;
1084 }
1085 break;
1086 case D_IFNDEF:
1087 done = -1;
1088 /* ANS X3.159-1989: #ifndef have only one identifier
1089 done = 0;
1090 */
1091 ifpush(); /* sets truth value to old truth value */
1092 toktyp = skipbl(tokval, 0);
1093 if (toktyp != T_IDENT) {
1094 pperr(232, 2);
1095 ifstack(truth) = 0;
1096 if (toktyp == '\n')
1097 done = 1;
1098 } else if (lookup(tokval, 0) != 0)
1099 ifstack(truth) = 0;
1100 else {
1101 ifstack(truth) &= 1;
1102 ifstack(true_seen) = 1;
1103 }
1104 break;
1105 case D_INCLUDE:
1106 done = 0;
1107 if (ifstack(truth)) {
1108 doincl(FALSE);
1109 done = 2;
1110 }
1111 break;
1112 case D_INCLUDE_NEXT:
1113 done = 0;
1114 if (ifstack(truth)) {
1115 doincl(TRUE);
1116 done = 2;
1117 }
1118 break;
1119 case D_DEFINE:
1120 done = 0;
1121 if (ifstack(truth)) {
1122 dodef(0);
1123 done = 1;
1124 }
1125 break;
1126 case D_UNDEF:
1127 done = 0;
1128 if (ifstack(truth)) {
1129 doundef(0);
1130 done = 1;
1131 }
1132 break;
1133 case D_LINE:
1134 done = 0;
1135 if (ifstack(truth)) {
1136 doline(1, (char *)0);
1137 done = 1;
1138 }
1139 break;
1140 case D_PRAGMA:
1141 done = 0;
1142 if (ifstack(truth)) {
1143 if (dopragma())
1144 /* returns non-zero if macro replacement is to occur
1145 * in the pragma line.
1146 */
1147 continue;
1148 done = 1;
1149 }
1150 break;
1151 case D_MODULE:
1152 done = 0;
1153 if (ifstack(truth)) {
1154 domodule();
1155 done = 1;
1156 }
1157 break;
1158 case D_LIST:
1159 list_flag = flg.list;
1160 break;
1161 case D_NOLIST:
1162 list_flag = 0;
1163 break;
1164 case D_IDENT:
1165 done = 0;
1166 if (ifstack(truth)) {
1167 doident();
1168 done = 1;
1169 }
1170 break;
1171 case D_ERROR:
1172 done = 0;
1173 if (ifstack(truth)) {
1174 doerror();
1175 done = 1;
1176 }
1177 break;
1178 case D_WARNING:
1179 done = 0;
1180 if (ifstack(truth)) {
1181 dowarning();
1182 done = 1;
1183 }
1184 break;
1185 default:
1186 if (!XBIT(123, 0x200000)) {
1187 if (ifstack(truth))
1188 pperror(236, tokval, 3);
1189 done = 0;
1190 } else {
1191 ptok("#");
1192 if (iswhite(*s_bl))
1193 ptok(" "); /* put back one whitespace if any present */
1194 /* toktyp == T_IDENT */
1195 if ((sp = lookup(tokval, 0)) != 0) {
1196 if (!macro_recur_check(sp)) {
1197 /* scan macro and substitute */
1198 int i;
1199 if ((i = subst(sp)) == EOF || i == T_SENTINEL) {
1200 toktyp = i;
1201 break;
1202 }
1203 }
1204 toktyp = T_NSIDENT;
1205 } else
1206 ptok(tokval);
1207 while ((toktyp = gtok(tokval, 1)) != EOF && toktyp != '\n')
1208 ptok(tokval);
1209 done = 1;
1210 }
1211 break;
1212 } /* switch */
1213 } /* else */
1214 if (done < 1)
1215 clreol(-done); /* clreol resets in_ftn_comment */
1216 else if (done == 1) {
1217 ptok("\n");
1218 in_ftn_comment = FALSE;
1219 }
1220 } /* for */
1221
1222 if (iftop != 0)
1223 pperr(218, 3);
1224
1225 if (!flg.es)
1226 (void)fseek(gbl.cppfil, 0L, 0);
1227
1228/* -M option: Print list of include files to stdout */
1229/* -MD option: Print list of include files to file <program>.d */
1230 if (XBIT(123, 2) || XBIT(123, 8)) {
1231 int count;
1232 if (gbl.dependfil == NULL) {
1233 if ((gbl.dependfil = tmpfile()) == NULL)
1234 errfatal(5);
1235 }
1236 count = strlen(gbl.module) + strlen(gbl.src_file) + 6;
1237 for (i = 0; i < incfiles; i++) {
1238 if ((count += (int)strlen(incllist[i])) >= 80) {
1239 fprintf(gbl.dependfil, "\\\n ");
1240 count = strlen(incllist[i]) + 3;
1241 }
1242 if (!XBIT(123, 0x40000))
1243 fprintf(gbl.dependfil, "%s ", incllist[i]);
1244 else
1245 fprintf(gbl.dependfil, "\"%s\" ", incllist[i]);
1246 }
1247 }
1248
1249 FREE(deftab);
1250 FREE(hashrec);
1251 /* FREE(inclstack); Do not free this, gbl.curr_file points to it */
1252 FREE(_ifs);
1253 FREE(linebuf);
1254
1255 if (incllist != 0) {
1256 FREE(incllist);
1257 }
1258}
1259
1260/** \brief
1261 * Format of pr_line output:
1262 * \# line "file_full_path" "from_stdinc"
1263 *
1264 * NB: -"form_stdinc" field is omitted in Fortran
1265 * -If you modify "System_Header", make sure
1266 * you modify get_line() in scan.c
1267 * (both the string and its length)
1268 */
1269static void
1270pr_line(const char *name, int line, LOGICAL from_stdinc)
1271{
1272 static INT last_inclev = -1;
1273
1274 /* -M option: Print list of include files to stdout */
1275 if (XBIT(123, 2) || XBIT(123, 0x20000000) || XBIT(123, 0x40000000))
1276 return;
1277
1278 if (pflag == 0) {
1279 if (inclev > 0 && inclev > last_inclev) {
1280 fprintf(gbl.cppfil, "# %d \"%s\"\n", inclstack[inclev - 1].lineno - 1,
1281 inclstack[inclev - 1].fname);
1282 }
1283
1284 fprintf(gbl.cppfil, "# %d \"%s\"\n", line, name);
1285 last_inclev = inclev;
1286 }
1287}
1288
1289static void
1290doline(int inflg, char *tokv)
1291{
1292 int toktyp;
1293 INT line;
1294 int isuns;
1295 char tokval[TOKMAX];
1296
1297 if (inflg) {
1298 toktyp = skipbl(tokval, 1);
1299 if (toktyp != T_PPNUM || tobinary(tokval, &isuns, &line) != 0) {
1300 pperr(228, 2);
1301 clreol(0);
1302 return;
1303 }
1304 } else {
1305 if (tobinary(tokv, &isuns, &line) != 0) {
1306 pperr(228, 2);
1307 clreol(0);
1308 return;
1309 }
1310 }
1311 toktyp = skipbl(tokval, 1);
1312 if (toktyp == '\n') {
1313 /* increments next time */
1314 inclstack[inclev].lineno = line - 1;
1315 return;
1316 } else if (toktyp == T_STRING) {
1317 tokval[0] = 0;
1318 tokval[strlen(tokval + 1)] = 0;
1319 strcpy(inclstack[inclev].fname, tokval + 1);
1320 if (!filename[0]) {
1321 strcpy(filename, inclstack[inclev].fname);
1322 gbl.file_name = filename;
1323 }
1324 /* DON'T CHANGE dirnam */
1325 /* increments next time */
1326 inclstack[inclev].lineno = line - 1;
1327 } else if (toktyp == T_IDENT) {
1328 strcpy(inclstack[inclev].fname, tokval);
1329 /* DON'T CHANGE dirnam */
1330 /* increments next time */
1331 inclstack[inclev].lineno = line - 1;
1332 } else
1333 pperr(228, 2);
1334 clreol(XBIT(123, 0x1000000) ? 0 : 1);
1335}
1336
1337static int
1338dopragma(void)
1339{
1340 char tokval[TOKMAX];
1341 int macro_repl;
1342
1343 if (!XBIT(123, 0x2000))
1344 macro_repl = 0;
1345 else
1346 macro_repl = 1;
1347 ptok("\n"); /* pragma in col 1 */
1348 ptok("#pragma");
1349 if (!XBIT(123, 0x8000)) {
1350 for (toktyp = gtok(tokval, 0); iswhite(toktyp); toktyp = gtok(tokval, 0)) {
1351 ptok(tokval);
1352 }
1353 if (toktyp != EOF && toktyp != '\n') {
1354 ptok(tokval);
1355 if (toktyp == T_IDENT) {
1356 if (strcmp(tokval, "omp") == 0 || strcmp(tokval, "acc") == 0 ||
1357 strcmp(tokval, "cuda") == 0 || strcmp(tokval, "ident") == 0 ||
1358 strcmp(tokval, "pgi") == 0) {
1359 macro_repl = 1;
1360 } else if (strcmp(tokval, "STDC") == 0)
1361 macro_repl = 0;
1362 }
1363 } else
1364 ptok("\n");
1365 }
1366 if (!macro_repl) {
1367 /* Pass pragmas through to compiler */
1368 while ((toktyp = gtok(tokval, 0)) != EOF && toktyp != '\n')
1369 ptok(tokval);
1370
1371 ptok("\n");
1372 }
1373 return macro_repl;
1374}

1376static void
1377doident(void)
1378{
1379 int toktyp;
1380 char tokval[TOKMAX];
1381
1382 /* syntax is #ident "string" */
1383 /* intent is for "string" to appear in the object file */
1384 toktyp = skipbl(tokval, 1);
1385 if (toktyp != T_STRING) {
1386 pperr(250, 2);
1387 tokval[0] = 0;
1388 tokval[strlen(tokval + 1)] = 0;
1389 /* tokval+1 is the string to put in the object file */
1390 }
1391 if (toktyp != '\n')
1392 clreol(1);
1393}

1425/** \param erf
1426 * <pre>
1427 *- 0: do NOT print msg 251;
1428 * -1/1: print msg 251(extraneous tokens ignored)
1429 * </pre>
1430 */
1431static void
1432clreol(int erf)
1433{
1434 int toktyp;
1435 char tokval[TOKMAX];
1436 int first = 0;
1437 LOGICAL is_fixed_form;
1438
1439 is_fixed_form = flg.freeform;
1440
1441 /* Scan to the end of the line (issue warnings if necessary) */
1442 while ((toktyp = gtok(tokval, 0)) != EOF && toktyp != '\n') {
1443 /* If fixed-form (72 column fortran) and in comment column, don't warn */
1444 if (is_fixed_form) {
1445 const int col = (lineptr - (linebuf + LINELEN + 1));
1446 if (col >= 73)
1447 first = 1; /* Set to one to prevent emitting a warning */
1448 }
1449 /* Only emit the error once (i.e., first has not been changed) */
1450 if (erf && first == 0 && !iswhite(toktyp)) {
1451 first = 1;
1452 pperr(251, 2);
1453 }
1454 }
1455
1456 if (toktyp != '\n')
1457 pperr(252, 4);
1458
1459 if (!XBIT(123, 0x80000))
1460 ptok("\n");
1461
1462 in_ftn_comment = FALSE;
1463}

1465static int
1466dlookup(char *name)
1467{
1468 static struct {
1469 const char *name;
1470 int val;
1471 } directives[] = {{"define", D_DEFINE},
1472 {"elif", D_ELIF},
1473 {"else", D_ELSE},
1474 {"endif", D_ENDIF},
1475 {"error", D_ERROR},
1476 {"ident", D_IDENT},
1477 {"if", D_IF},
1478 {"ifdef", D_IFDEF},
1479 {"ifndef", D_IFNDEF},
1480 {"include", D_INCLUDE},
1481 {"include_next", D_INCLUDE_NEXT},
1482 {"line", D_LINE},
1483 {"list", D_LIST},
1484 {"module", D_MODULE},
1485 {"nolist", D_NOLIST},
1486 {"pragma", D_PRAGMA},
1487 {"undef", D_UNDEF},
1488 {"warning", D_WARNING},
1489 {"DEFINE", D_DEFINE},
1490 {"ELIF", D_ELIF},
1491 {"ELSE", D_ELSE},
1492 {"ENDIF", D_ENDIF},
1493 {"ERROR", D_ERROR},
1494 {"IDENT", D_IDENT},
1495 {"IF", D_IF},
1496 {"IFDEF", D_IFDEF},
1497 {"IFNDEF", D_IFNDEF},
1498 {"INCLUDE", D_INCLUDE},
1499 {"INCLUDE_NEXT", D_INCLUDE_NEXT},
1500 {"LINE", D_LINE},
1501 {"LIST", D_LIST},
1502 {"MODULE", D_MODULE},
1503 {"NOLIST", D_NOLIST},
1504 {"PRAGMA", D_PRAGMA},
1505 {"UNDEF", D_UNDEF},
1506 {"WARNING", D_WARNING},
1507 {0, 0}};
1508 int i;
1509
1510 for (i = 0; directives[i].name; ++i)
1511 if (strcmp(directives[i].name, name) == 0)
1512 return (directives[i].val);
1513 return (0);
1514}

1516static int
1517inlist(int *list, int nl, char *value, char *macbuf)
1518{
1519 int i;
1520
1521 for (i = 0; i < nl; ++i)
1522 if (strcmp(macbuf + list[i], value) == 0)
1523 return (i + 1);
1524 if (strcmp(value, "__VA_ARGS__") == 0)
1525 return -1;
1526 return (0);
1527}
1528
1529/** \brief
1530 Default behavior:
1531 Add whitespace at the beginning and end of the macro body, and
1532 between tokens in the macro body.
1533
1534 Behavior Modified by:
1535 - -Mx,123,x20:
1536 Do NOT add whitespace at the beginning, between and end of the
1537 macro body.
1538 - -Mx,123,x200:
1539 Add whitespace at beginning, end and between tokens in the macro
1540 body. Do NOT add whitespace between tokens when OUTSIDE of a
1541 macro body.
1542 - -Mx,123,x800:
1543 Do NOT collapse consecutive whitespace ('cpp' mode).
1544 */
1545static void
1546dodef(int cmdline)
1547{
1548 int toktyp;
1549 PPSYM *sp;
1550 int nformals;
1551 char *macbuf;
1552 int macsize;
1553 int formals[FORMALMAX];
1554 char *p, *q, *r, *s;
1555 int defp;
1556 int i, n;
1557 int funclike;
1558 char tokval[TOKMAX];
1559 int prevtok;
1560 char tmpbuf[TOKMAX];
1561 int needspace = 1;
1562
1563 NEW(macbuf, char, MACMAX);
1564 macsize = MACMAX;
1565
1566 /* Tell nextok() that we are processing a #define */
1567 in_dodef = TRUE;
1568
1569 /* fetch symbol after #define */
1570 p = macbuf;
1571 toktyp = skipbl(tokval, 0);
1572 if (toktyp != T_IDENT) {
1573 pperr(215, 2); /* illegal macro name is warning in cpp */
1574 clreol(0);
1575 goto ret;
1576 }
1577 /* look up the name */
1578 if ((sp = lookup(tokval, 1)) == 0) {
1579 /* must be predefined macro */
1580 clreol(0);
1581 goto ret;
1582 }
1583 /* here we need to read the definition */
1584 nformals = 0;
1585 funclike = 0;
1586 toktyp = gtok(tokval, 0);
1587 if (toktyp == '(') {
1588 int delim; /* just lex'd a delimitter, ( or , */
1589 delim = 1;
1590 funclike = F_FUNCLIKE;
1591 toktyp = skipbl(tokval, 0);
1592 for (;;) {
1593 if (toktyp == ')')
1594 break;
1595 if (toktyp != T_IDENT) {
1596 if (toktyp == T_OP && strcmp(tokval, "...") == 0) {
1597 /* next token better be ')' */
1598 toktyp = skipbl(tokval, 0);
1599 if (toktyp != ')') {
1600 pperror(224, "...", 3);
1601 clreol(0);
1602 goto nulldef;
1603 }
1604 if (delim) {
1605 funclike |= F_VA_ARGS;
1606 break;
1607 }
1608 if (XBIT(123, 0x1000) && !delim && nformals) {
1609 funclike |= F_VA_REST;
1610 break;
1611 }
1612 pperror(224, "...", 3);
1613 clreol(0);
1614 goto nulldef;
1615 } else {
1616 pperror(224, tokval, 3);
1617 clreol(0);
1618 goto nulldef;
1619 }
1620 }
1621 delim = 0;
1622 /* save formal */
1623 if (nformals + 1 > FORMALMAX)
1624 pperror(234, &deftab[sp->name], 3);
1625 else {
1626
1627#define GROW_MACBUF(amt, p) \
1628 if (1) { \
1629 int _n, _i, _offs; \
1630 _n = amt; \
1631 if (_n < MACMAX) \
1632 _n = MACMAX; \
1633 _offs = p - macbuf; \
1634 _i = _offs + amt; \
1635 NEED(_i, macbuf, char, macsize, macsize + _n); \
1636 p = macbuf + _offs; \
1637 } else
1638
1639 n = strlen(tokval) + 1;
1640 /* Check for duplicate formal parameter */
1641 i = inlist(formals, nformals, tokval, macbuf);
1642 if (i) {
1643 if (i < 0)
1644 pperr(235, 3);
1645 else
1646 pperror(257, &deftab[sp->name], 2);
1647 }
1648 GROW_MACBUF(n, p);
1649 strcpy(p, tokval);
1650 formals[nformals++] = p - macbuf;
1651 p += n;
1652 }
1653 toktyp = skipbl(tokval, 0);
1654 if (toktyp == ',') {
1655 toktyp = skipbl(tokval, 0);
1656 delim = 1;
1657 continue;
1658 }
1659 if (toktyp == '\n') {
1660 pperror(242, &deftab[sp->name], 3);
1661 goto nulldef;
1662 }
1663 }
1664 toktyp = gtok(tokval, 0);
1665 }
1666
1667 /*
1668 * now nformals has # formals, formals has formals, and token is first
1669 * after macro def
1670 */
1671
1672 if (iswhite(toktyp)) {
1673 toktyp = skipbl(tokval, 0);
1674 needspace = 0;
1675 }
1676 if (toktyp == '\n') {
1677 nulldef:
1678 if (sp->value &&
1679 (sp->nformals != nformals || ((sp->flags & F_FUNCLIKE) != funclike) ||
1680 deftab[sp->value]))
1681 pperror(221, &deftab[sp->name], 2); /* redef is warning in cpp */
1682 else if (sp->value)
1683 pperror(222, &deftab[sp->name], 1);
1684 sp->value = strstore("");
1685 sp->flags |= funclike;
1686 sp->nformals = nformals;
1687 if ((XBIT(122, 0x10000) && !cmdline) || (XBIT(122, 0x40000) && cmdline))
1688 putmac(sp);
1689 goto ret;
1690 }
1691 /* collect definition */
1692 defp = p - macbuf;
1693 prevtok = 0;
1694
1695 /* Add whitespace to the beginning of the macro body */
1696 if (!iswhite(toktyp) && !XBIT(123, 0x20)) {
1697 GROW_MACBUF(2, p);
1698 *p++ = WHITESPACE;
1699 needspace = 0;
1700 }
1701
1702 for (;;) {
1703 if (toktyp == EOF) {
1704 pperror(209, &deftab[sp->name], 3);
1705 goto ret;
1706 }
1707 /* replace multiple white space by single space */
1708 if (iswhite(toktyp)) {
1709 toktyp = skipbl(tokval, 0);
1710 GROW_MACBUF(2, p);
1711 *p++ = ' ';
1712 needspace = 0;
1713 goto cont;
1714 }
1715
1716 tmpbuf[0] = tokval[1]; /* character if T_CHAR toktyp */
1717 tmpbuf[1] = '\0';
1718
1719 if (toktyp == T_IDENT &&
1720 (i = inlist(formals, nformals, tokval, macbuf)) == 0 &&
1721 prevtok == '#') {
1722 pperror(260, tokval, 3);
1723 clreol(0);
1724 goto ret;
1725 } else if (toktyp == T_IDENT &&
1726 (i = inlist(formals, nformals, tokval, macbuf)) != 0) {
1727 /* we found a formal */
1728 GROW_MACBUF(2, p);
1729 if (i == -1) { /* __VA_ARGS__ */
1730 if ((funclike & F_VA_ARGS) == 0) {
1731 pperr(235, 3);
1732 clreol(0);
1733 goto ret;
1734 }
1735 i = VA_ARGS;
1736 } else if ((funclike & F_VA_REST) && i == nformals) {
1737 i = VA_REST;
1738 }
1739 /* ident preceeded by '#' is string-ized */
1740 if (prevtok == '#') {
1741 while (iswhite(*--p)) /* delete '#' */
1742 ;
1743 --p; /* ENDTOKEN */
1744 *p++ = i;
1745 *p++ = STRINGIZE;
1746 } else if (prevtok == T_CONCAT) {
1747 /* delete white space before this token */
1748 while (iswhite(*--p))
1749 ;
1750 if (MASK(*p) == ENDTOKEN)
1751 --p;
1752 ++p;
1753 *p++ = i;
1754 *p++ = CONCAT1;
1755 /* delete white space after this token */
1756 toktyp = skipbl(tokval, 0);
1757 /*prevtok = T_CONCAT;*/
1758 prevtok = 0;
1759 goto cont;
1760 } else {
1761
1762 /* Add whitespace between tokens in the macro body */
1763 if (!XBIT(123, 0x20) && needspace) {
1764 GROW_MACBUF(2, p);
1765 *p++ = WHITESPACE;
1766 needspace = 0;
1767 } else
1768 needspace = 1;
1769
1770 /* make space for the next 3 */
1771 GROW_MACBUF(3, p);
1772 *p++ = i;
1773 /* comes last since subst scans backwards */
1774 *p++ = ARGST;
1775 *p++ = ENDTOKEN;
1776 }
1777 } else if (toktyp == T_CONCAT) {
1778 /* concatenation */
1779 needspace = 0;
1780 while (p > macbuf + defp && iswhite(*--p))
1781 ;
1782 /* ## directive placed at beginning of replacement list */
1783 if (p == macbuf + defp) {
1784 pperr(259, 3);
1785 clreol(0);
1786 goto ret;
1787 }
1788 if (MASK(*p) == ENDTOKEN)
1789 --p;
1790 if (MASK(*p) == ARGST || MASK(*p) == CONCAT1)
1791 *p = CONCAT;
1792 ++p;
1793 toktyp = skipbl(tokval, 0);
1794 /* ## directive placed at end of replacement list */
1795 if (toktyp == '\n') {
1796 pperr(259, 3);
1797 goto ret;
1798 }
1799 prevtok = T_CONCAT;
1800 goto cont;
1801 } else if (toktyp == T_CHAR &&
1802 (i = inlist(formals, nformals, tmpbuf, macbuf)) != 0) {
1803
1804 if (!XBIT(123, 0x40)) { /* -Xs */
1805 /* "no macro replacement within a character constant" */
1806 pperror(261, CNULL, 2);
1807
1808 n = strlen(tokval);
1809 GROW_MACBUF(n + 1, p);
1810 strcpy(p, tokval);
1811 p += n;
1812 *p++ = ENDTOKEN;
1813 } else {
1814 /* "macro replacement within a character constant" */
1815 pperror(262, CNULL, 2);
1816
1817 GROW_MACBUF(2 + 3, p);
1818 *p++ = '\'';
1819 *p++ = i;
1820 /* comes last since subst scans backwards */
1821 *p++ = ARGST;
1822 *p++ = '\'';
1823 *p++ = ENDTOKEN;
1824 sp->flags |= F_CHAR;
1825 }
1826 } else if (toktyp == T_STRING) {
1827 int delim;
1828 n = strlen(tokval);
1829 GROW_MACBUF(n + 1, p);
1830 q = p;
1831
1832 s = &tokval[1];
1833 *p++ = tokval[0];
1834 delim = tokval[0];
1835 while (*s && *s != delim) {
1836
1837 while (*s == ' ')
1838 *p++ = *s++;
1839 r = &tmpbuf[0];
1840 while (*s && *s != ' ' && *s != delim) {
1841 *r++ = *s++;
1842 if (*(s - 1) == '\\')
1843 *r++ = *s++;
1844 }
1845 *r = '\0';
1846
1847 i = inlist(formals, nformals, tmpbuf, macbuf);
1848 if (i > 0) {
1849 if (!XBIT(123, 0x40)) { /* -Xs, -Xt */
1850 /* "no macro replacement within a string literal" */
1851 p = q;
1852 strcpy(p, tokval);
1853 p += n;
1854 *p++ = ENDTOKEN;
1855
1856 sp->flags &= ~F_CHAR;
1857 prevtok = toktyp;
1858 toktyp = gtok(tokval, 0);
1859 goto cont;
1860 }
1861
1862 if (XBIT(123, 0x80)) { /* -Xt */
1863 if (!(sp->flags & F_CHAR))
1864 /* "macro replacement within a string literal" */
1865 pperror(264, CNULL, 2);
1866 }
1867
1868 GROW_MACBUF(2, p);
1869 *p++ = i;
1870 /* comes last since subst scans backwards */
1871 *p++ = ARGST;
1872 *p++ = ENDTOKEN;
1873 sp->flags |= F_CHAR;
1874 } else {
1875 strcpy(p, tmpbuf);
1876 p += strlen(tmpbuf);
1877 }
1878 }
1879 if (*s)
1880 *p++ = *s;
1881 *p++ = ENDTOKEN;
1882 } else if (/*toktyp != '#' &&*/ toktyp != T_CONCAT) {
1883
1884 /* Add whitespace between tokens in the macro body */
1885 if (!XBIT(123, 0x20) && needspace) {
1886 GROW_MACBUF(2, p);
1887 *p++ = WHITESPACE;
1888 needspace = 0;
1889 } else
1890 needspace = 1;
1891
1892 n = strlen(tokval);
1893 GROW_MACBUF(n + 1, p);
1894 strcpy(p, tokval);
1895 p += n;
1896 *p++ = ENDTOKEN;
1897 }
1898 prevtok = toktyp;
1899 toktyp = gtok(tokval, 0);
1900 cont:
1901 if (toktyp == '\n')
1902 break;
1903 }
1904 /* strip trailing space */
1905 --p;
1906 while (iswhite(*p))
1907 --p;
1908 *++p = 0;
1909 /* install definition */
1910 /* compare definitions */
1911 if (sp->value &&
1912 (((sp->flags & F_FUNCLIKE) != funclike) || sp->nformals != nformals ||
1913 strcmp(macbuf + defp, &deftab[sp->value])))
1914 pperror(221, &deftab[sp->name], 2); /* warning in cpp */
1915
1916 /* Test if the names of the formal parameters have been changed */
1917 if (sp->value && nformals == sp->nformals &&
1918 (sp->flags & F_FUNCLIKE) == funclike) {
1919 for (i = 0; i < nformals; i++) {
1920 char argbuf[16 + 1];
1921 if (strcmp(&macbuf[formals[i]], &deftab[sp->formals[i]])) {
1922 sprintf(argbuf, "%d", i + 1);
1923 error(258, 2, startline, argbuf, &deftab[sp->name]);
1924 }
1925 }
1926 }
1927 /* Save names of formal parameters */
1928 for (i = 0; i < nformals; i++) {
1929 sp->formals[i] = strstore(&macbuf[formals[i]]);
1930 }
1931 sp->value = strstore(macbuf + defp);
1932 sp->nformals = nformals;
1933 sp->flags |= funclike;
1934 if ((XBIT(122, 0x10000) && !cmdline) || (XBIT(122, 0x40000) && cmdline))
1935 putmac(sp);
1936 if (DBGBIT(2, 0x80))
1937 dumpmac(sp);
1938
1939ret:
1940 FREE(macbuf);
1941#ifdef DUMPTAB
1942 dumptab();
1943#endif
1944
1945 in_dodef = FALSE;
1946}

1948static void
1949doincl(LOGICAL include_next)
1950{
1951 int toktyp;
1952 char buff[MAX_PATHNAME_LEN];
1953 char *p;
1954 int type;
1955 char tokval[TOKMAX];
1956 int missing = 0;
1957
1958 /* parse file name */
1959 toktyp = skipbl(tokval, 1);
1960 /* ### there is a problem here; "" filename not really a string */
1961 if (toktyp != T_STRING && toktyp != '<') {
1962 pperr(227, 3);
1963 return;
1964 }
1965 if (toktyp == T_STRING) {
1966 char delim;
1967 delim = *tokval;
1968 strncpy(buff, tokval + 1, MAX_PATHNAME_LEN);
1969 if ((p = strchr(buff, delim)) != NULL)
1970 *p = 0;
1971 buff[MAX_PATHNAME_LEN - 1] = 0;
1972 type = 0;
1973 } else {
1974 /* toktyp == '<' */
1975 buff[0] = 0;
1976 for (;;) {
1977 toktyp = gtok(tokval, 0);
1978 if (toktyp == '>')
1979 break;
1980 if (toktyp == '\n') {
1981 missing = 1;
1982 pperr(256, 2);
1983 break;
1984 }
1985 if (toktyp == EOF) {
1986 pperr(237, 3);
1987 break;
1988 }
1989 strncat(buff, tokval, MAX_PATHNAME_LEN);
1990 }
1991 buff[MAX_PATHNAME_LEN - 1] = 0;
1992 type = 1;
1993 }
1994 if (!missing)
1995 clreol(1);
1996
1997 _doincl(buff, type, include_next);
1998
1999}

2001#ifdef FLANG1_ACCPP_UNUSED
2002/** \brief
2003 * Check if fullname is a file in a standard include directory.
2004 */
2005static LOGICAL
2006is_in_stdinc(const char *fullname)
2007{
2008 const char *dirs = flg.stdinc;
2009
2010 /* This x-bit disables our distinguishing system header files from normal
2011 * includes. */
2012 if (XBIT(123, 0x800000))
2013 return FALSE;
2014
2015 /* Was stdinc even set? */
2016 if (dirs == NULL || dirs == (char *)1)
2017 return FALSE;
2018
2019 /* The stdinc path contains directories separated by DIRSEP. */
2020 while (TRUE) {
2021 const char *path;
2022
2023 /* Skip leading separators. */
2024 if (*dirs == DIRSEP) {
2025 dirs++;
2026 continue;
2027 }
2028
2029 /* End of path reached. */
2030 if (*dirs == '\0')
2031 break;
2032
2033 /* Remember beginning of path and advance dirs to the end. */
2034 path = dirs;
2035 while ((*dirs != '\0') && (*dirs != DIRSEP))
2036 dirs++;
2037
2038 /* Check for a prefix match. */
2039 if (strncmp(fullname, path, (dirs - path)) == 0)
2040 return TRUE;
2041 }
2042 return FALSE;
2043}
2044#endif
2045
2046/** \brief
2047 * Add fullname to the list of include files in incllist.
2048 *
2049 * This list is used to generate build system dependencies with the -M, -MM,
2050 * -MD, and -MMD options.
2051 *
2052 * The fullname buffer will be modified by this function.
2053 *
2054 * The file should be added to inclstack with a correct sys bit before calling
2055 * this function. The inclstack is inspected to implement -MM and -MMD
2056 * correctly.
2057 */
2058static void
2059add_to_incllist(char *fullname)
2060{
2061 INT i;
2062
2063 /* Bail early if dependency generation is not enabled. */
2064 if (!XBIT(123, 2) && /* -M / -MM */
2065 !XBIT(123, 8) && /* -MD / -MMD */
2066 !XBIT(123, 0x20000000) && /* -MT */
2067 !XBIT(123, 0x40000000)) /* -MQ */
2068 return;
2069
2070 /* When -MM or -MMD are active, skip system headers and any file included
2071 * from a system header directly or indirectly.
2072 *
2073 * This means we check the entire include stack for system headers. This
2074 * matches the behavior of GCC 3.1+ and Clang.
2075 */
2076 if (XBIT(123, 0x4000))
2077 for (i = inclev; i >= 0; i--)
2078 if (inclstack[i].from_stdinc)
2079 return;
2080
2081 /* Remove duplicates. */
2082 for (i = 0; i < incfiles; i++)
2083 if (strcmp(incllist[i], fullname) == 0)
2084 return;
2085
2086 /* Finally copy fullname to the end of incllist. */
2087 if (incllist == 0) {
2088 inclsize = 20;
2089 NEW(incllist, INCLENTRY, inclsize);
2090 } else {
2091 NEED(incfiles + 1, incllist, INCLENTRY, inclsize, inclsize + 20);
2092 }
2093 strcpy(incllist[incfiles], fullname);
2094 incfiles++;
2095}

2097/** \param type:
2098 * <pre>
2099 * -0 -- "file_name"
2100 * -1 -- <file_name>
2101 * </pre>
2102 */
2103static void
2104_doincl(char *name, int type, LOGICAL include_next)
2105{
2106 char fullname[MAX_PATHNAME_LEN];
2107 int i;
2108
2109 NEED(inclev + 2, inclstack, INCLSTACK, incsize, incsize + MAXINC);
2110
2111 /* look for included file: */
2112
2113 if (type == 0 && (idir.last == -1 || !include_next)) {
2114 /* look first in directory containing current included or base file */
2115 strcpy(dirwork, inclstack[inclev].dirname);
2116 i = strlen(dirwork) - 1;
2117 if (i >= 0 && dirwork[i] == '/')
2118 dirwork[i] = 0;
2119 if (fndpath(name, fullname, MAX_PATHNAME_LEN, dirwork) == 0) {
2120 idir.last = 0;
2121 goto found;
2122 }
2123 }
2124 i = 1;
2125 if (include_next && idir.last >= 0)
2126 i = idir.last + 1;
2127 for (; i <= idir.cnt; i++)
2128 if (fndpath(name, fullname, MAX_PATHNAME_LEN, INCLPATH(i)) == 0) {
2129 idir.last = i;
2130 goto found;
2131 }
2132
2133 pperror(206, name, 4); /* cpp just continues, but why?? */
2134 return;
2135
2136found:
2137 /* we need to increment the line # for this level */
2138 ++inclstack[inclev].lineno;
2139 ++inclev;
2140 if ((ifp = inclstack[inclev].ifp = fopen(fullname, "r")) == NULL) {
2141 --inclev; /* failed to open file so retract changes */
2142 --inclstack[inclev].lineno;
2143 error(2, 4, 0, fullname, CNULL);
2144 return;
2145 }
2146
2147 /* Test for recursive includes */
2148 for (i = 0; i < inclev - 1; i++) {
2149 if (!strcmp(inclstack[i].fname, fullname)) {
2150 if (++inclstack[i].count > 37) {
2151 pperror(265, fullname, 4);
2152 }
2153 break;
2154 }
2155 }
2156 if (XBIT(122, 0x20000)) {
2157 if (gbl.curr_file != prevfile || startline != prevline + 1)
2158 printf("\n// %s:%d\n", gbl.curr_file, startline);
2159 prevfile = gbl.curr_file;
2160 prevline = startline;
2161 printf("#include%s %s\n", include_next ? "_next" : "", fullname);
2162 }
2163
2164 strcpy(inclstack[inclev].fname, fullname);
2165 dirnam(inclstack[inclev].fname, inclstack[inclev].dirname);
2166 inclstack[inclev].count = 1;
2167 gbl.curr_file = inclstack[inclev].fname;
2168 inclstack[inclev].lineno = 0;
2169 inclstack[inclev].from_stdinc = FALSE;
2170 inclstack[inclev].path_idx = idir.last;
2171
2172 pr_line(fullname, 1, inclstack[inclev].from_stdinc);
2173 add_to_incllist(fullname);
2174}

2300static int
2301subst(PPSYM *sp)
2302{
2303 char *p, *q, *r, *r1;
2304 int nformals;
2305 int toktyp;
2306 char *actuals[FORMALMAX];
2307 int nactuals;
2308 char *argbuf;
2309 char *oldargbuf;
2310 char *targbuf;
2311 char *blank;
2312 char *argp;
2313 char *fstart;
2314 char tmp;
2315 int nlpar;
2316 int i, waswhite, instr;
2317 char tokval[TOKMAX];
2318 int argbufsize, targbufsize, newsize;
2319 int nl;
2320 int savech;
2321 size_t len;
2322
2323#ifdef SUBST
2324 fprintf(stderr, "subst(%s)\n", deftab + sp->name);
2325#endif
2326 NEW(argbuf, char, ARGMAX + 1);
2327 argbufsize = ARGMAX + 1;
2328
2329 NEW(targbuf, char, TARGMAX + 1);
2330 targbufsize = TARGMAX + 1;
2331
2332 blank = strdup(""); /* required for assigning to actuals */
2333
2334 /* Do not replace 'C' or 'c' in first column, yes, some people might define
2335 * a macro named 'C' or 'c'... people like myself. --ignoramous
2336 */
2337 if (lineptr == (linebuf + LINELEN + 1)) {
2338 tmp = *(linebuf + LINELEN); /* First char in col 1 */
2339 if (tmp == 'c' || tmp == 'C') {
2340 if (tmp == 'c') /* Use ptok to skip to next token */
2341 ptok("c");
2342 else
2343 ptok("C");
2344 FREE(argbuf);
2345 FREE(targbuf);
2346 FREE(blank);
2347 return 0;
2348 }
2349 }
2350
2351 if (sp == hashrec + lineloc) {
2352 sprintf(argbuf, "%d", inclstack[inclev].lineno);
2353 pbchar(ENDTOKEN);
2354 pbstr(argbuf);
2355 FREE(argbuf);
2356 FREE(targbuf);
2357 FREE(blank);
2358 return 0;
2359 } else if (sp == hashrec + fileloc) {
2360 /* escape backslashes in file name */
2361 argbuf[0] = '\"';
2362 for (p = inclstack[inclev].fname, i = 1; p && *p; p++, i++) {
2363 if (*p == '\\')
2364 argbuf[i++] = '\\';
2365 argbuf[i] = *p;
2366 }
2367 argbuf[i++] = '\"';
2368 argbuf[i] = '\0';
2369 pbchar(ENDTOKEN);
2370 pbstr(argbuf);
2371#ifdef SUBST
2372 fprintf(stderr, "subst(%s) returns\n", deftab + sp->name);
2373#endif
2374 FREE(argbuf);
2375 FREE(targbuf);
2376 FREE(blank);
2377 return 0;
2378 }
2379 argbuf[argbufsize - 1] = 0;
2380 p = &deftab[sp->value];
2381 nformals = sp->nformals;
2382 if (!(sp->flags & F_FUNCLIKE)) {
2383 /* macro has no args; just substitute */
2384 mac_push(sp, lineptr);
2385 pbstr(p);
2386#ifdef SUBST
2387 fprintf(stderr, "subst(%s) returns\n", deftab + sp->name);
2388#endif
2389 FREE(argbuf);
2390 FREE(targbuf);
2391 FREE(blank);
2392 return 0;
2393 }
2394 /* scan arguments */
2395 i = 0;
2396 nl = 0;
2397 for (toktyp = gtok(tokval, 0); isblank(toktyp) || toktyp == '\n';
2398 toktyp = gtok(tokval, 0)) {
2399 ++i;
2400 if (toktyp == '\n')
2401 ++nl;
2402 }
2403 if (toktyp != '(') { /* funclike not recognized */
2404 if (toktyp == EOF) {
2405 ptok(&deftab[sp->name]);
2406 ptok("\n");
2407 FREE(argbuf);
2408 FREE(targbuf);
2409 FREE(blank);
2410 return EOF;
2411 }
2412
2413 if (toktyp == '#') {
2414 /* macro has no args; do NOT substitute */
2415 ptok(&deftab[sp->name]);
2416 FREE(argbuf);
2417 FREE(targbuf);
2418 FREE(blank);
2419 return (T_SENTINEL);
2420 }
2421 pbstr(tokval);
2422 if (nl) { /* FS#14715 need to preserve newline */
2423 pbchar('\n');
2424 cur_line++;
2425 }
2426 if (toktyp == T_NSIDENT)
2427 pbchar(NOSUBST);
2428 if (i)
2429 pbchar(' ');
2430 pbstr(&deftab[sp->name]);
2431 pbchar(NOFUNC);
2432#ifdef SUBST
2433 fprintf(stderr, "subst(%s) returns\n", deftab + sp->name);
2434#endif
2435 FREE(argbuf);
2436 FREE(targbuf);
2437 FREE(blank);
2438 return 0;
2439 }
2440 argp = argbuf;
2441 nactuals = 0;
2442 nlpar = 1;
2443 fstart = argp;
2444 for (;;) {
2445 toktyp = gtok(tokval, 0);
2446 if (toktyp == ')') {
2447 --nlpar;
2448 if (nlpar == 0)
2449 break;
2450 } else if (toktyp == '(')
2451 ++nlpar;
2452 else if (toktyp == ',') {
2453 if (nlpar == 1) {
2454 /* save actual */
2455 if (nactuals + 1 > FORMALMAX)
2456 pperror(233, &deftab[sp->name], 3);
2457 else if (argp - argbuf >= argbufsize - 1) {
2458 oldargbuf = argbuf;
2459 newsize = argp - argbuf + ARGMAX;
2460 GROW_ARGBUF(argbuf, argp, fstart, argbufsize, newsize);
2461 update_actuals(actuals, nactuals, oldargbuf, argbuf);
2462 }
2463 if (argp == fstart) {
2464 /* macro(,) case */
2465 *fstart = 0;
2466 ++argp;
2467 } else {
2468 while (iswhite(*fstart))
2469 ++fstart;
2470 --argp;
2471 while (iswhite(*argp) && argp > fstart)
2472 --argp;
2473 *++argp = 0;
2474 ++argp;
2475 }
2476 actuals[nactuals++] = fstart;
2477 fstart = argp;
2478 continue;
2479 }
2480 } else if (toktyp == EOF || toktyp == T_SENTINEL) {
2481 pperror(209, &deftab[sp->name], 3);
2482 FREE(argbuf);
2483 FREE(targbuf);
2484 FREE(blank);
2485 return toktyp;
2486 }
2487 if (argp - argbuf + (int)strlen(tokval) + 2 > argbufsize - 1) {
2488 newsize = argbufsize + (int)strlen(tokval) + 2 + ARGMAX;
2489 oldargbuf = argbuf;
2490 GROW_ARGBUF(argbuf, argp, fstart, argbufsize, newsize);
2491 update_actuals(actuals, nactuals, oldargbuf, argbuf);
2492 }
2493 if (iswhite(toktyp) || toktyp == '\n') {
2494 if ((argp > fstart) && *(argp - 1) != ' ') {
2495 if (argp - argbuf + 1 > argbufsize - 1) {
2496 newsize = argp - argbuf + 1 + ARGMAX;
2497 oldargbuf = argbuf;
2498 GROW_ARGBUF(argbuf, argp, fstart, argbufsize, newsize);
2499 update_actuals(actuals, nactuals, oldargbuf, argbuf);
2500 }
2501 *argp++ = ' ';
2502 }
2503 continue;
2504 }
2505 if (toktyp == T_NSIDENT)
2506 *argp++ = NOSUBST;
2507 strcpy(argp, tokval);
2508 argp += strlen(tokval);
2509 *argp++ = ENDTOKEN;
2510 }
2511 /* save last actual */
2512 if (nactuals + 1 > FORMALMAX)
2513 pperror(233, &deftab[sp->name], 3);
2514 else if (argp - argbuf >= argbufsize - 1) {
2515 oldargbuf = argbuf;
2516 newsize = argp - argbuf + 1 + ARGMAX;
2517 GROW_ARGBUF(argbuf, argp, fstart, argbufsize, newsize);
2518 update_actuals(actuals, nactuals, oldargbuf, argbuf);
2519 }
2520 if (argp == fstart) {
2521 *fstart = 0;
2522 } else {
2523 while (iswhite(*fstart))
2524 ++fstart;
2525 --argp;
2526 while (iswhite(*argp))
2527 --argp;
2528 *++argp = 0;
2529 }
2530 actuals[nactuals++] = fstart;
2531
2532 /* substitute */
2533 if (nformals != nactuals) {
2534 if (!(nformals == 0 && nactuals == 1 && *actuals[0] == '\0')) {
2535 if ((sp->flags & (F_VA_ARGS | F_VA_REST))) {
2536 ; /* ok */
2537 } else
2538 pperror(205, &deftab[sp->name], 2);
2539 }
2540 for (i = nactuals; i < nformals; i++)
2541 actuals[i] = blank;
2542 }
2543 q = p;
2544 p += strlen(p); /* end of macro text */
2545 savlptr = lineptr;
2546 for (;;) {
2547 /* look for "funny" characters */
2548 while ((*--p & 0x80) == 0 && p >= q)
2549 pbchar(*p);
2550 if (p < q)
2551 break;
2552 switch (MASK(*p)) {
2553 int itmp;
2554 int iend;
2555
2556 case STRINGIZE:
2557 --p;
2558 if (MASK(*p) == VA_ARGS) {
2559 if (nactuals <= nformals) {
2560 pbchar('"');
2561 pbchar('"');
2562 break;
2563 }
2564 i = nactuals - 1;
2565 iend = nformals;
2566 } else if (MASK(*p) == VA_REST) {
2567 /* NOTE: nformals includes the 'rest' argument */
2568 if (nactuals < nformals) {
2569 pbchar('"');
2570 pbchar('"');
2571 break;
2572 }
2573 i = nactuals - 1;
2574 iend = nformals - 1;
2575 } else
2576 iend = i = *p - 1;
2577 pbchar('"');
2578 for (; i >= iend; i--) {
2579 r = r1 = actuals[i];
2580 r += strlen(r);
2581 waswhite = 0;
2582 instr = 0;
2583 --r;
2584 while (iswhite(*r) && r >= r1)
2585 --r;
2586 while (r >= r1) {
2587 if (iswhite(*r) && !instr)
2588 waswhite = 1;
2589 else {
2590 if (waswhite) {
2591 waswhite = 0;
2592 pbchar(' ');
2593 }
2594 if (instr) {
2595 if (*r == '\\') {
2596 pbchar(*r);
2597 pbchar('\\');
2598 } else if (*r == '"') {
2599 pbchar(*r);
2600 pbchar('\\');
2601 if (r > r1 && r[-1] != '\\')
2602 instr = 0;
2603 } else if ((*r & 0x80) == 0)
2604 pbchar(*r);
2605 } else if (*r == '"') {
2606 instr = 1;
2607 pbchar(*r);
2608 pbchar('\\');
2609 } else if ((*r & 0x80) == 0)
2610 pbchar(*r);
2611 }
2612 --r;
2613 }
2614 if (i != iend)
2615 pbstr(", ");
2616 }
2617 pbchar('"');
2618 break;
2619
2620 case CONCAT:
2621 /* delete trailing ENDTOKEN */
2622 --p;
2623 if (MASK(*p) == VA_ARGS) {
2624 if (nactuals <= nformals)
2625 continue;
2626 i = nactuals - 1;
2627 } else if (MASK(*p) == VA_REST) {
2628 /* NOTE: nformals includes the 'rest' argument */
2629 if (nactuals <= nformals)
2630 continue;
2631 i = nactuals - 1;
2632 } else
2633 i = *p - 1;
2634 itmp = strlen(actuals[i]);
2635 if (itmp && MASK(actuals[i][itmp - 1]) == ENDTOKEN) {
2636 savech = actuals[i][itmp - 1];
2637 actuals[i][itmp - 1] = 0;
2638 } else
2639 savech = 0;
2640 goto concat_shared;
2641
2642 case CONCAT1:
2643 /* delete trailing ENDTOKEN */
2644 --p;
2645 savech = 0;
2646 concat_shared:
2647 if (MASK(*p) == VA_ARGS) {
2648 if (nactuals <= nformals) {
2649 if (XBIT(123, 0x1000)) {
2650 /* `##' before __VA_ARGS__ discards the preceding
2651 * sequence of non-whitespace characters and ','
2652 * from the macro definition iff '...' args are not
2653 * present.
2654 */
2655 char *qq;
2656 for (qq = p - 1; qq >= q; qq--) {
2657 switch (MASK(*qq)) {
2658 case WHITESPACE:
2659 continue;
2660 case ',':
2661 p = qq;
2662 break;
2663 default:
2664 break;
2665 }
2666 break;
2667 }
2668 }
2669 continue;
2670 }
2671 for (i = nactuals - 1; i >= nformals; i--) {
2672 pbstr(actuals[i]);
2673 if (i != nformals) {
2674 pbchar(ENDTOKEN);
2675 pbchar(',');
2676 }
2677 }
2678 } else if (MASK(*p) == VA_REST) {
2679 /* NOTE: nformals includes the 'rest' argument */
2680 if (nactuals < nformals) {
2681 /* `##' before a rest argument that is empty discards the
2682 * preceding sequence of non-whitespace characters from
2683 * the macro definition. (If another macro argument
2684 * precedes, none of it is discarded.)
2685 */
2686 char *qq;
2687 for (qq = p - 1; qq >= q; qq--) {
2688 switch (MASK(*qq)) {
2689 case WHITESPACE:
2690 continue;
2691 case CONCAT:
2692 *qq = ARGST;
2693 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
2694 case ARGST:
2695 qq++;
2696 break;
2697 default:
2698 break;
2699 }
2700 break;
2701 }
2702 p = qq;
2703 continue;
2704 }
2705 for (i = nactuals - 1; i >= nformals - 1; i--) {
2706 pbstr(actuals[i]);
2707 if (i != nformals - 1) {
2708 pbchar(ENDTOKEN);
2709 pbchar(',');
2710 }
2711 }
2712 } else if (*p <= nactuals) {
2713 if (MASK(*actuals[*p - 1]) == NOSUBST) {
2714 pbstr(actuals[*p - 1] + 1);
2715 } else {
2716 pbstr(actuals[*p - 1]);
2717 }
2718 if (savech)
2719 actuals[i][itmp - 1] = savech;
2720 }
2721 break;
2722
2723 case WHITESPACE:
2724 case ENDTOKEN:
2725 break;
2726
2727 case PRAGMAOP:
2728 if (nactuals != 1) {
2729 pperror(269, "requires one argument which must be a string", 3);
2730 break;
2731 }
2732 r = r1 = actuals[0];
2733 if (*r1 == 'L')
2734 r1++;
2735
2736 /* Special case: The first (and only) argument to _Pragma does not start
2737 * with a leading '"'. Try to expand and see if we get a '"', if not,
2738 * fail.
2739 */
2740 if (*r1 != '"') {
2741 /* Expand the argument (can only be one argument) */
2742 pbchar(SENTINEL);
2743 pbstr(actuals[0]);
2744 toktyp = gtok(tokval, 1);
2745 if (toktyp != T_STRING)
2746 goto pragmaop_err;
2747
2748 /* Save the string to a buffer, and terminate with ENDTOKEN */
2749 argp = targbuf;
2750 fstart = argp;
2751 if (argp - targbuf + (int)strlen(tokval) + 2 > targbufsize - 1) {
2752 newsize = argp - targbuf + (int)strlen(tokval) + 2 + TARGMAX;
2753 GROW_ARGBUF(targbuf, argp, fstart, targbufsize, newsize);
2754 }
2755 r = r1 = strcpy(argp, tokval);
2756 len = strlen(r);
2757 r[len + 0] = ENDTOKEN; /* " ENDTOKEN \0 */
2758 r[len + 1] = '\0';
2759
2760 /* Sanity test: Better be the SENTINEL we pushed */
2761 toktyp = gtok(tokval, 0);
2762
2763 /* Remove any literal prefixes or the leading quote */
2764 if (*r1 == 'L')
2765 ++r1;
2766 if ((toktyp != T_SENTINEL) || *r1 != '"') {
2767 pragmaop_err:
2768 while (toktyp != T_SENTINEL) /* Erase the sentinel that we added */
2769 toktyp = gtok(tokval, 0);
2770 pperror(269, "requires one argument which must be a string", 3);
2771 break;
2772 }
2773 }
2774 if (!XBIT(123, 0x2000000))
2775 pbchar('\n');
2776 r += strlen(r);
2777 r -= 3; /* last character - backup before " ENDTOKEN */
2778 r1++; /* skip " */
2779 while (r >= r1) {
2780 pbchar(*r);
2781 if (*r == '"' && r >= r1 && *(r - 1) == '\\')
2782 /* replace the escape sequence \" with " */
2783 r--;
2784 else if (*r == '\\' && r >= r1 && *(r - 1) == '\\')
2785 /* replace the escape sequence \\ with \ */
2786 r--;
2787 r--;
2788 }
2789 pbstr("#pragma ");
2790 pbchar('\n'); /* pragma in col 1 */
2791 break;
2792
2793 case VA_ARGS:
2794 case VA_REST:
2795 pperr(235, 3);
2796 break;
2797
2798 case ARGST:
2799 --p;
2800 if (MASK(*p) == VA_ARGS) {
2801 if (nactuals <= nformals)
2802 continue;
2803 argp = targbuf;
2804 fstart = argp;
2805 pbchar(SENTINEL);
2806 for (i = nactuals - 1; i >= nformals; i--) {
2807 pbstr(actuals[i]);
2808 if (i != nformals) {
2809 pbchar(ENDTOKEN);
2810 pbchar(',');
2811 }
2812 }
2813 goto expand_actual;
2814 } else if (MASK(*p) == VA_REST) {
2815 /* NOTE: nformals includes the 'rest' argument */
2816 if (nactuals < nformals)
2817 continue;
2818 argp = targbuf;
2819 fstart = argp;
2820 pbchar(SENTINEL);
2821 for (i = nactuals - 1; i >= nformals - 1; i--) {
2822 pbstr(actuals[i]);
2823 if (i != nformals - 1) {
2824 pbchar(ENDTOKEN);
2825 pbchar(',');
2826 }
2827 }
2828 goto expand_actual;
2829 }
2830 if (*p > nactuals)
2831 continue;
2832 /* we have to expand this actual */
2833 argp = targbuf;
2834 fstart = argp;
2835 pbchar(SENTINEL);
2836 pbstr(actuals[*p - 1]);
2837 expand_actual:
2838 while ((toktyp = gtok(tokval, 1)) != T_SENTINEL) {
2839 /* save actual */
2840 if (toktyp == EOF) {
2841 pperror(209, &deftab[sp->name], 3);
2842 FREE(argbuf);
2843 FREE(targbuf);
2844 FREE(blank);
2845 return EOF;
2846 }
2847 if (argp - targbuf + (int)strlen(tokval) + 1 > targbufsize - 1) {
2848 newsize = argp - targbuf + (int)strlen(tokval) + 1 + TARGMAX;
2849 GROW_ARGBUF(targbuf, argp, fstart, targbufsize, newsize);
2850 }
2851 if (toktyp == T_NSIDENT)
2852 *argp++ = NOSUBST;
2853 strcpy(argp, tokval);
2854 argp += strlen(tokval);
2855 if (!(sp->flags & F_CHAR))
2856 *argp++ = ENDTOKEN;
2857 }
2858 if (argp != targbuf) {
2859 while (iswhite(*fstart))
2860 ++fstart;
2861 --argp;
2862 while (iswhite(*argp))
2863 --argp;
2864 *++argp = 0;
2865 pbstr(fstart);
2866 }
2867 break;
2868 default:
2869 interr("accpp: unexpected marker", startline, 3);
2870 break;
2871 }
2872 }
2873
2874 mac_push(sp, savlptr);
2875#ifdef SUBST
2876 fprintf(stderr, "subst(%s) returns\n", deftab + sp->name);
2877#endif
2878 FREE(argbuf);
2879 FREE(targbuf);
2880 FREE(blank);
2881 return (0);
2882}

3086/* insflg -
3087 * 0: lookup only, do NOT add if not found
3088 * Returns: NULL - not previously def'd
3089 * !NULL - previously def'd
3090 * 1: Add macro if not already defined
3091 * Returns: NULL - already def'd
3092 * !NULL - added ok
3093 */
3094static PPSYM *
3095lookup(const char *name, int insflg)
3096{
3097 int i;
3098 char *cp;
3099 INT p, q;
3100 INT l, m;
3101 char buff[MAXIDLEN + 1];
3102
3103 /* need to make sure not defining a predef macro */
3104 i = 0;
3105 l = m = (INT)0;
3106
3107 strncpy(buff, name, MAXIDLEN);
3108 buff[MAXIDLEN] = 0;
3109 /*
3110 * break name into 3 byte chunks, sum them together, take remainder
3111 * modulo table size
3112 */
3113 cp = buff;
3114 while (*cp != '\0') {
3115 if (i == 3) {
3116 i = 0;
3117 m += l;
3118 l = (INT)0;
3119 }
3120 ++i;
3121 l <<= 8;
3122 l |= MASK(*cp);
3123 cp++;
3124 }
3125 m += l;
3126 i = m % HASHSIZ;
3127 for (q = 0, p = hashtab[i]; p != 0; q = p, p = hashrec[p].next) {
3128 if (strcmp(buff, &deftab[hashrec[p].name]) == 0) {
3129 if (insflg) {
3130 if (hashrec[p].flags & F_PREDEF) {
3131 /* can't def */
3132 pperror(247, name, 2);
3133 return NULL;
3134 }
3135 }
3136 if (hashrec[p].nformals != -1) /* is it 'defined'? */
3137 return &hashrec[p];
3138 return NULL;
3139 }
3140 }
3141 if (!insflg)
3142 return (NULL);
3143 /* allocate new record */
3144 if (hashrec == NULL) {
3145 nhash = 100;
3146 NEW(hashrec, PPSYM, nhash);
3147 next_hash = 2;
3148 p = 1;
3149 } else {
3150 p = next_hash;
3151 ++next_hash;
3152 NEED(next_hash, hashrec, PPSYM, nhash, nhash + 100);
3153 }
3154 hashrec[p].value = 0;
3155 hashrec[p].name = strstore(buff);
3156 hashrec[p].flags = 0;
3157 hashrec[p].nformals = 0;
3158 if (q == 0) {
3159 hashrec[p].next = hashtab[i];
3160 hashtab[i] = p;
3161 } else {
3162 hashrec[q].next = p;
3163 hashrec[p].next = 0;
3164 }
3165 return &hashrec[p];
3166}

3168static void
3169delete(const char *name)
3170{
3171 int i, j;
3172 INT l, m;
3173 INT p, q;
3174 const char *cp;
3175
3176 i = j = 0;
3177 l = m = (INT)0;
3178
3179 /*
3180 * break name into 3 byte chunks, sum them together, take remainder
3181 * modulo table size
3182 */
3183 cp = name;
3184 while (j < MAXIDLEN && *cp != '\0') {
3185 if (i == 3) {
3186 i = 0;
3187 m += l;
3188 l = (INT)0;
3189 }
3190 ++i;
3191 ++j;
3192 l <<= 8;
3193 l |= *cp++;
3194 }
3195 m += l;
3196 i = m % HASHSIZ;
3197 for (q = 0, p = hashtab[i]; p != 0; q = p, p = hashrec[p].next)
3198 if (strncmp(name, &deftab[hashrec[p].name], MAXIDLEN) == 0)
3199 goto found;
3200 return;
3201found:
3202 if (hashrec[p].flags & F_PREDEF) {
3203 /* can't undef */
3204 pperror(248, name, 2);
3205 return;
3206 }
3207 /* delete record */
3208 if (q == 0) /* first in list */
3209 hashtab[i] = hashrec[p].next;
3210 else
3211 hashrec[q].next = hashrec[p].next;
3212}

3214static void
3215ptok(const char *tok)
3216{
3217 FILE *fp;
3218 static int state = 1;
3219 static int nchars;
3220 static int needspace = 0;
3221 static int leading = 1;
3222 char *tokchr = strdup(tok);
3223 char *tokptr = tokchr;
3224
3225 /* -M option: Print list of include files to stdout */
3226 if (XBIT(123, 2) || XBIT(123, 0x20000000) || XBIT(123, 0x40000000))
3227 return;
3228
3229 /* keep track of where compiler thinks we are */
3230 fp = gbl.cppfil;
3231 if (*tokchr == '\n') {
3232 if (state == 1 && !XBIT(123, 0x80000))
3233 return;
3234 state = 1; /* next token starts a new line */
3235 nchars = 0;
3236 ++cur_line;
3237 needspace = 0;
3238 }
3239 /* if starting a new line, make sure line # and file are correct */
3240 else if (state) {
3241 state = 0;
3242 leading = 1;
3243 /* make sure next line and file are correct */
3244 if (strcmp(cur_fname, inclstack[inclev].fname) || cur_line != startline) {
3245 strcpy(cur_fname, inclstack[inclev].fname);
3246 cur_line = startline;
3247 cur_from_stdinc = inclstack[inclev].from_stdinc;
3248 if (startline != 1)
3249 pr_line(cur_fname, startline, cur_from_stdinc);
3250 }
3251 }
3252 if (!XBIT(123, 0x20) && !XBIT(123, 0x200)) {
3253 if (needspace && !iswhite(*tokchr) && MASK(*tokchr) != WHITESPACE &&
3254 *tokchr != '\n') {
3255 (void)putc(' ', fp);
3256 ++nchars;
3257 needspace = 0;
3258 }
3259 }
3260
3261 if (MASK(*tokchr) == WHITESPACE) {
3262 *tokchr = ' ';
3263 }
3264
3265 /* Suppress duplicate whitespaces added by macro expansion */
3266 if (!XBIT(123, 0x800) && !leading && !needspace && iswhite(*tokchr)) {
3267 ++nchars;
3268 if (!(*(++tokchr)))
3269 return;
3270 }
3271
3272 if (leading && !iswhite(*tokchr))
3273 leading = 0;
3274
3275 needspace = !(iswhite(*tokchr) || *tokchr == '\n');
3276 while (*tokchr) {
3277 (void)putc(*tokchr++, fp);
3278 ++nchars;
3279 }
3280 FREE(tokptr);
3281}

3360#define CHECK(t) \
3361 { \

3367static INT
3368doparse(void)
3369{
3370 INT i;
3371 PTOK tmp;
3372
3373 token = gettoken();
3374 if (token == Eoln) {
3375 pperr(226, 3);
3376 return (1);
3377 }
3378 syntaxerr = 0;
3379 parse(-1, &tmp);
3380 i = PTOK_ISNZ(tmp);
3381 if (syntaxerr) {
3382 if (token != Eoln)
3383 clreol(0);
3384 } else

3388
3389#define UCONV \
3390 if (PTOK_ISUNS(left) || PTOK_ISUNS(right)) \
3391 PTOK_ISUNS(left) = 1; \
3392 else \
3393 PTOK_ISUNS(left) = 0
3394
3395/** \brief
3396 * parse "current" expression and return value computed
3397 * by constant folding it.
3398 */
3399static void
3400parse(int rbp, PTOK *tk)
3401{
3402 int op;
3403 LOGICAL valid_left = FALSE;
3404 int t;
3405 PTOK right, tmp, left;
3406 do {
3407 op = token;
3408 tmp = tokenval;
3409 token = gettoken();
3410
3411 if (!valid_left) {
3412 valid_left = TRUE;
3413 op = PT[op].nud;
3414 if (op == 0)
3415 goto syntax_error;
3416 } else {
3417 if (PT[op].led == 0)
3418 goto syntax_error;
3419 }
3420
3421 if (op != Number && op != Defined && op != Predicate)
3422 parse(PT[op].rbp, &right);
3423
3424 switch (op) {
3425 case Number:
3426 left = tmp;
3427 break;
3428 case Lparen:
3429 left = right;
3430 CHECK(Rparen);
3431 break;
3432 case Defined:
3433 case Predicate:
3434 t = token;
3435 if (token == Lparen)
3436 token = gettoken();
3437 left = tokenval;
3438 /* smt: according to ansi, "the argument to defined() shall be an
3439 * identifier" */
3440 if (toktyp != T_IDENT)
3441 goto syntax_error;
3442 token = gettoken();
3443
3444 if (t == Lparen)
3445 CHECK(Rparen);
3446 break;
3447 case Mult:
3448 UCONV;
3449 PTOK_MUL(left, right); /* left *= right */
3450 break;
3451 case Divide:
3452 UCONV;
3453 if (!PTOK_ISUNS(left))
3454 PTOK_DIV(left, right); /* left /= right */
3455 else
3456 PTOK_UDIV(left, right);
3457 break;
3458 case Mod:
3459 UCONV;
3460 if (!PTOK_ISUNS(left))
3461 PTOK_MOD(left, right); /* left %= right */
3462 else
3463 PTOK_UMOD(left, right);
3464 break;
3465 case Plus:
3466 UCONV;
3467 PTOK_ADD(left, right); /* left += right */
3468 break;
3469 case Minus:
3470 UCONV;
3471 PTOK_SUB(left, right); /* left -= right */
3472 break;
3473 case Lshift:
3474 case Rshift:
3475 UCONV;
3476#ifdef TM_REVERSE_SHIFT
3477 if (PTOK_ISNEG(right)) {
3478 PTOK_NEG(right, right);
3479 op = (Lshift + Rshift) - op;
3480 }
3481#endif
3482 if (op == Lshift)
3483 PTOK_LSHIFT(left, right);
3484 else if (PTOK_ISUNS(left))
3485 PTOK_URSHIFT(left, right);
3486 else
3487 PTOK_CRSHIFT(left, right);
3488 break;
3489 case Lt:
3490 UCONV;
3491 if (!PTOK_ISUNS(left))
3492 PTOK_LOGLT(left, right);
3493 else
3494 PTOK_LOGULT(left, right);
3495 break;
3496 case Gt:
3497 UCONV;
3498 if (!PTOK_ISUNS(left))
3499 PTOK_LOGGT(left, right);
3500 else
3501 PTOK_LOGUGT(left, right);
3502 break;
3503 case Le:
3504 UCONV;
3505 if (!PTOK_ISUNS(left))
3506 PTOK_LOGLE(left, right);
3507 else
3508 PTOK_LOGULE(left, right);
3509 break;
3510 case Ge:
3511 UCONV;
3512 if (!PTOK_ISUNS(left))
3513 PTOK_LOGGE(left, right);
3514 else
3515 PTOK_LOGUGE(left, right);
3516 break;
3517 case Eq:
3518 UCONV;
3519 PTOK_LOGEQ(left, right);
3520 break;
3521 case Ne:
3522 UCONV;
3523 PTOK_LOGNE(left, right);
3524 break;
3525 case And:
3526 UCONV;
3527 PTOK_AND(left, right);
3528 break;
3529 case Xor:
3530 UCONV;
3531 PTOK_XOR(left, right);
3532 break;
3533 case Or:
3534 UCONV;
3535 PTOK_OR(left, right);
3536 break;
3537 case Comma:
3538 UCONV;
3539/* Ansi restriction, comma not allowed in directive,
3540 Section 3.4 */
3541 PTOK_ASSN(left, right);
3542 break;
3543 case Minusx:
3544 PTOK_ISUNS(left) = PTOK_ISUNS(right);
3545 PTOK_NEG(left, right);
3546 break;
3547 case Not:
3548 PTOK_LNOT(left, right);
3549 PTOK_ISUNS(left) = 0;
3550 break;
3551 case Compl:
3552 PTOK_ISUNS(left) = PTOK_ISUNS(right);
3553 PTOK_BNOT(left, right);
3554 break;
3555 case Plusx:
3556 PTOK_ISUNS(left) = PTOK_ISUNS(right);
3557 PTOK_ASSN(left, right);
3558 break;
3559 case Andand:
3560 PTOK_ANDAND(left, right);
3561 PTOK_ISUNS(left) = 0;
3562 break;
3563 case Oror:
3564 PTOK_OROR(left, right);
3565 PTOK_ISUNS(left) = 0;
3566 break;
3567 case Question:
3568 CHECK(Colon);
3569 parse(PT[Question].rbp, &tmp);
3570 if (PTOK_ISUNS(left) || PTOK_ISUNS(tmp))
3571 PTOK_ISUNS(left) = 1;
3572 if (PTOK_ISNZ(left))
3573 PTOK_ASSN(left, right);
3574 else
3575 PTOK_ASSN(left, tmp);
3576 break;
3577 default:
3578 goto syntax_error;
3579 }
3580 } while (PT[token].lbp > rbp);
3581
3582 *tk = left;
3583 return;
3584
3585syntax_error:
3586 pperr(226, 3);
3587 syntaxerr = 1;
3588 token = Eoln;
3589 PTOK_ASSN32(tmp, 1);
3590 PTOK_ISUNS(tmp) = 0;
3591 *tk = tmp;
3592}
3593
3594static int
3595gettoken(void)
3596{
3597 static int ifdef = 0;
3598 char *s;
3599 PPSYM *sp;
3600 char tokval[TOKMAX];
3601 int i, c;
3602 INT t;
3603
3604 for (;;) {
3605 toktyp = skipbl(tokval, !ifdef);
3606 if (toktyp == '\n')
3607 return Eoln; /* end of #if */
3608 again:
3609 switch (toktyp) {
3610 case T_OP:
3611 switch (*tokval) {
3612 case '|':
3613 if (tokval[1] == '|')
3614 return Oror;
3615 goto illch;
3616 case '&':
3617 if (tokval[1] == '&')
3618 return Andand;
3619 goto illch;
3620 case '>':
3621 if (tokval[1] == '>' && tokval[2] != '=')
3622 return Rshift;
3623 if (tokval[1] == '=')
3624 return Ge;
3625 goto illch;
3626 case '<':
3627 if (tokval[1] == '<' && tokval[2] != '=')
3628 return Lshift;
3629 if (tokval[1] == '=')
3630 return Le;
3631 goto illch;
3632 case '=':
3633 if (tokval[1] == '=')
3634 return Eq;
3635 goto illch;
3636 case '!':
3637 if (tokval[1] == '=')
3638 return Ne;
3639 goto illch;
3640 default:
3641 goto illch;
3642 }
3643 case '#':
3644 /* could be an AT&T predicate */
3645 toktyp = skipbl(tokval, 0);
3646 if (toktyp == '\n') {
3647 pperr(253, 2);
3648 return Eoln;
3649 }
3650 if (toktyp != T_IDENT) {
3651 pperr(253, 2);
3652 goto again;
3653 }
3654 predicate(tokval);
3655 ifdef = 2;
3656 return Predicate;
3657 case '|':
3658 return (Or);
3659 case '&':
3660 return (And);
3661 case '>':
3662 return (Gt);
3663 case '<':
3664 return (Lt);
3665 case '!':
3666 return (Not);
3667 case '+':
3668 return (Plus);
3669 case '-':
3670 return (Minus);
3671 case '*':
3672 return (Mult);
3673 case '/':
3674 return (Divide);
3675 case '%':
3676 return (Mod);
3677 case '^':
3678 return (Xor);
3679 case '?':
3680 return (Question);
3681 case ':':
3682 return (Colon);
3683 case '~':
3684 return (Compl);
3685 case '(':
3686 return (Lparen);
3687 case ')':
3688 return (Rparen);
3689 case ',':
3690 return (Comma);
3691 case T_PPNUM:
3692/* parse number */
3693#if defined(PPNUM_IS_32)
3694 if (tobinary(tokval, &PTOK_ISUNS(tokenval), &PTOK_V(tokenval)) != 0)
3695#else
3696 if (tobinary64(tokval, &PTOK_ISUNS(tokenval), PTOK_V(tokenval)))
3697#endif
3698 {
3699 pperr(254, 3);
3700 PTOK_ASSN32(tokenval, 0);
3701 }
3702 return Number;
3703 case T_IDENT:
3704 if (0 == strcmp(tokval, "defined")) {
3705 ifdef = 1;
3706 return (Defined);
3707 } else if (ifdef == 1) {
3708 sp = lookup(tokval, 0);
3709 ifdef = 0;
3710 PTOK_ASSN32(tokenval, sp && sp->value != 0);
3711 PTOK_ISUNS(tokenval) = 0;
3712 return (Number);
3713 } else {
3714 ifdef = 0;
3715 PTOK_ASSN32(tokenval, predarg(tokval));
3716 PTOK_ISUNS(tokenval) = 0;
3717 return Number;
3718 }
3719 break;
3720 case T_WCHAR:
3721 s = tokval + 2;
3722 goto commchar;
3723 case T_CHAR:
3724 s = tokval + 1;
3725 commchar:
3726 /* multi-char const? */
3727 i = 0;
3728 PTOK_ASSN32(tokenval, 0);
3729 PTOK_ISUNS(tokenval) = 0;
3730 while ((c = *s) != '\'' && i < 4) {
3731 ++s;
3732 ++i;
3733 PTOK_LSHIFT32(tokenval, 8);
3734 if (c == '\\') {
3735 switch (c = *s++) {
3736 case 'a':
3737 t = '\007';
3738 break;
3739 case 'b':
3740 t = '\b';
3741 break;
3742 case 'f':
3743 t = '\f';
3744 break;
3745 case 'n':
3746 t = '\n';
3747 break;
3748 case 'r':
3749 t = '\r';
3750 break;
3751 case 't':
3752 t = '\t';
3753 break;
3754 case 'v':
3755 t = '\v';
3756 break;
3757 case 'x':
3758 t = 0;
3759 while (ishex(*s)) {
3760 t *= 16;
3761 c = *s++;
3762 if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'f')
3763 t += c - 'a' + 10;
3764 else if (c >= 'A' && c <= 'F')
3765 t += c - 'A' + 10;
3766 else
3767 t += c - '0';
3768 }
3769 break;
3770 default:
3771 if (c >= '0' && c <= '7') {
3772 t = c - '0';
3773 if (*s >= '0' && *s <= '7') {
3774 t = t * 8 + (*s++ - '0');
3775 if (*s >= '0' && *s <= '7') {
3776 t = t * 8 + (*s++ - '0');
3777 }
3778 }
3779 } else {
3780 t = c;
3781 }
3782 break;
3783 }
3784 PTOK_OR32(tokenval, t);
3785 } else
3786 PTOK_OR32(tokenval, c);
3787 }
3788 if (i == 0 || i > 4) {
3789 pperr(24, 3);
3790 }
3791#ifndef CHAR_IS_UNSIGNED
3792 if (i == 1) {
3793 if (PTOK_BTEST32(tokenval, 0x80)) {
3794 PTOK_OR32(tokenval, 0xffffff00);
3795 PTOK_SEXTEND32(tokenval);
3796 }
3797 } else if (i == 2) {
3798 if (PTOK_BTEST32(tokenval, 0x8000)) {
3799 PTOK_OR32(tokenval, 0xffff0000);
3800 PTOK_SEXTEND32(tokenval);
3801 }
3802 }
3803#endif
3804 PTOK_ISUNS(tokenval) = 0;
3805 return (Number);
3806 case T_STRING:
3807 case T_WSTRING:
3808 pperr(255, 3);
3809 PTOK_ASSN32(tokenval, 0);
3810 PTOK_ISUNS(tokenval) = 0;
3811 return Number;
3812
3813 default:
3814 illch:
3815 pperr(255, 3);
3816 continue;
3817 }
3818 }
3819}
3820
3821static INT
3822tobinary(char *st, int *isuns, INT *value)
3823{
3824 int radix;
3825 int r;
3826 char c;
3827 char *cp;
3828
3829 c = *(cp = st);
3830 radix = 10;
3831 if (c == '0') {
3832 if (cp[1] == 'x' || cp[1] == 'X') {
3833 radix = 16;
3834 cp += 2;
3835 while (ishex(*cp))
3836 ++cp;
3837 } else {
3838 radix = 8;
3839 while (isdigit(*cp))
3840 ++cp;
3841 }
3842 } else
3843 while (isdigit(*cp))
3844 ++cp;
3845 *isuns = 0;
3846 if (radix == 16)
3847 st += 2;
3848 r = atoxi(st, value, (int)(cp - st), radix);
3849 if (r == -1) {
3850 if (radix == 16)
3851 st -= 2;
3852 c = *cp;
3853 *cp = 0;
3854 pperror(27, st, 3);
3855 *cp = c;
3856 st = cp;
3857 return -1;
3858 } else if (r != 0) { /* overflow */
3859 if (radix == 16)
3860 st -= 2;
3861 c = *cp;
3862 *cp = 0;
3863 pperror(23, st, 2);
3864 *cp = c;
3865 if (radix == 16)
3866 st += 2;
3867 }
3868 if (*cp == 'l' || *cp == 'L' || *cp == 'u' || *cp == 'U') {
3869 if (*cp == 'u' || *cp == 'U')
3870 *isuns = 1;
3871 ++cp;
3872 if (*cp == 'l' || *cp == 'L' || *cp == 'u' || *cp == 'U') {
3873 if (*cp == 'u' || *cp == 'U')
3874 *isuns = 1;
3875 ++cp;
3876 }
3877 }
3878
3879 /* smt */
3880 /* Check illegal integer */
3881 if (cp != st + strlen(st)) {
3882 pperror(27, st, 3);
3883 return -1;
3884 }
3885 if (r == -1) {
3886 if (radix == 16)
3887 st -= 2;
3888 c = *cp;
3889 *cp = 0;
3890 pperror(27, st, 3);
3891 *cp = c;
3892 st = cp;
3893 return -1;
3894 }
3895 if ((*value & 0x80000000) || r == -2)
3896 *isuns = 1;
3897 return 0;
3898}

3900static INT
3901tobinary64(char *st, int *isuns, DBLINT64 value)
3902{
3903 int radix;
3904 int r;
3905 char c;
3906 char *cp;
3907
3908 c = *(cp = st);
3909 radix = 10;
3910 if (c == '0') {
3911 if (cp[1] == 'x' || cp[1] == 'X') {
3912 radix = 16;
3913 cp += 2;
3914 while (ishex(*cp))
3915 ++cp;
3916 } else {
3917 radix = 8;
3918 while (isdigit(*cp))
3919 ++cp;
3920 }
3921 } else
3922 while (isdigit(*cp))
3923 ++cp;
3924 *isuns = 0;
3925 if (radix == 16)
3926 st += 2;
3927 r = atoxi64(st, value, (int)(cp - st), radix);
3928 if (r == -1) {
3929 if (radix == 16)
3930 st -= 2;
3931 c = *cp;
3932 *cp = 0;
3933 pperror(27, st, 3);
3934 *cp = c;
3935 st = cp;
3936 return -1;
3937 } else if (r != 0) { /* overflow */
3938 if (radix == 16)
3939 st -= 2;
3940 c = *cp;
3941 *cp = 0;
3942 pperror(23, st, 2);
3943 *cp = c;
3944 if (radix == 16)
3945 st += 2;
3946 }
3947 /* Process any suffix which may follow the constant -- can be
3948 * followed by L and/or U in any order or case
3949 */
3950 switch (*cp) {
3951 case 'l':
3952 case 'L':
3953 /* suffix begins with L */
3954 ++cp;
3955 switch (*cp) {
3956 case 'u':
3957 case 'U':
3958 /***** LU *****/
3959 *isuns = 1;
3960 ++cp;
3961 if (*cp == 'l' || *cp == 'L') {
3962 /***** LUL *****/
3963 ++cp;
3964 }
3965 break;
3966 case 'l':
3967 case 'L':
3968 /***** LL *****/
3969 ++cp;
3970 if (*cp == 'u' || *cp == 'U') {
3971 /***** LLU *****/
3972 *isuns = 1;
3973 ++cp;
3974 }
3975 break;
3976 }
3977 break;
3978
3979 case 'u':
3980 case 'U':
3981 /* suffix begins with U */
3982 *isuns = 1;
3983 ++cp;
3984 if (*cp == 'l' || *cp == 'L') {
3985 /***** UL *****/
3986 ++cp;
3987 if (*cp == 'l' || *cp == 'L') {
3988 /***** ULL *****/
3989 ++cp;
3990 }
3991 }
3992 break;
3993 }
3994
3995 /* smt */
3996 /* Check illegal integer */
3997 if (cp != st + strlen(st)) {
3998 pperror(27, st, 3);
3999 return -1;
4000 }
4001 if (r == -1) {
4002 if (radix == 16)
4003 st -= 2;
4004 c = *cp;
4005 *cp = 0;
4006 pperror(27, st, 3);
4007 *cp = c;
4008 st = cp;
4009 return -1;
4010 }
4011 if ((value[0] & 0x80000000) || r == -2)
4012 *isuns = 1;
4013 return 0;
4014}

4016/* expflag == 1: expand token from macro */
4017static int
4018gtok(char *tokval, int expflag)
4019{
4020 PPSYM *sp;
4021 int toktyp;
4022 int i;
4023 int comment = 0;
4024
4025again:
4026 /* -C option: Pass comments through the preprocessor */
4027 comment = 0;
4028 if (XBIT(123, 1) && flg.es == TRUE) {
4029 flg.es = FALSE; /* Remove comments from directives */
4030 comment = 1;
4031 }
4032 toktyp = nextok(tokval, 0);
4033
4034 if (comment)
4035 flg.es = TRUE;
4036
4037 if (toktyp == T_NOFIDENT)
4038 toktyp = T_IDENT;
4039 else if (toktyp == T_IDENT && expflag && (sp = lookup(tokval, 0)) != 0) {
4040 if (!macro_recur_check(sp)) {
4041 /* scan macro and substitute */
4042 if ((i = subst(sp)) == EOF || i == T_SENTINEL)
4043 return i;
4044 goto again;
4045 }
4046 toktyp = T_NSIDENT;
4047 }
4048 return (toktyp);
4049}
4050
4051static int
4052findtok(char *tokval, int truth)
4053{
4054 int i;
4055 int state;
4056 PPSYM *sp;
4057 int toktyp;
4058
4059 state = 1;
4060
4061 if (truth) {
4062 for (;;) {
4063 toktyp = nextok(tokval, 1);
4064 if (toktyp == EOF)
4065 return (EOF);
4066 if (toktyp == '#' && state) {
4067 return (T_POUND);
4068 }
4069 if (!isblank(toktyp))
4070 state = 0; /* allow whitespace before '#' directives */
4071 if (toktyp == T_NOFIDENT)
4072 toktyp = T_IDENT;
4073 else if (toktyp == T_IDENT && (sp = lookup(tokval, 0)) != 0) {
4074 if (!macro_recur_check(sp)) {
4075 /* scan macro and substitute */
4076 if ((i = subst(sp)) == EOF || i == T_SENTINEL)
4077 return i;
4078 continue;
4079 }
4080 toktyp = T_NSIDENT;
4081 }
4082 if (toktyp == '\n') {
4083 state = 1;
4084 in_ftn_comment = FALSE;
4085 }
4086 ptok(tokval);
4087 }
4088 } else {
4089 for (;;) {
4090 toktyp = nextok(tokval, 0);
4091 if (toktyp == EOF)
4092 return (EOF);
4093 if (toktyp == '#' && state) {
4094 return (T_POUND);
4095 }
4096 if (!isblank(toktyp))
4097 state = 0; /* allow whitespace before '#' directives */
4098 if (toktyp == '\n') {
4099 state = 1;
4100 in_ftn_comment = FALSE;
4101 }
4102 }
4103 }
4104}

4106#define inchar() (lineptr < lineend ? *lineptr++ : _nextline())

4108static int
4109nextok(char *tokval, int truth)
4110{

4115 int toktyp;
4116 int retval;
4117 char *savtokval = tokval;
4118 char *comment_ptr;
4119 int dot_seen;
4120
4121again:
4122 if ((c = inchar()) == EOF) {
4123 retval = EOF;
4124 goto nextok_ret;
4125 }
4126 *tokval++ = c;
4127 switch (c) {
4128 case '$':
4129 if (XBIT(123, 0x100000))
4130 goto defret;
4131 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
4132
4133 /* Identifier or Fortran 'C' comment.
4134 * If this is Fortran and a 'C', it might be an identifier or comment.
4135 * The 'c' or 'C' must be in the first column (fixed-form)
4136 * to be recognized here as Fortran comment.
4137 */

4139 case 'c':
4140 in_ftn_comment = TRUE;

4143 /* c in column 1, start of old-style comment */
